title: green and white vegetable salad
directions: Remove large leaves of broccoli and cut off tough end of lower stalks. Wash thoroughly. Cut into 1-inch pieces or smaller. Combine all vegetables in a large bowl.

title: prune bread
directions: Cover prunes with water.
Cover and simmer about 40 minutes. Drain prunes, saving prune water.
Pit prunes and mash.
Add sugar, eggs, salt, vanilla and prune water.
Sift together and add the flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Bake 1 hour.

title: catfish mulldown
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in a large heavy pot. Remove bacon and set aside. Layer remaining ingredients, beginning with potatoes. Cook at low heat for about 2 hours.

title: lemon lace cake
directions: You will need 1 paper doily.

title: cushaw pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, salt and cloves together. Add beaten eggs; add cushaw and cream, then put into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: hamburger-noodle casserole
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in a large skillet. Add next 4 ingredients and simmer. Cook noodles and drain.
In a large casserole dish, place a layer of noodles on bottom of dish.
Cover with meat layer, then cheese. Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fried okra
directions: Heat oil.
Slice okra across the pod into small pieces. Combine flour, salt and pepper in a small bag; shake okra in bag until well coated.
Drop several pieces at a time into deep hot fat until brown.
Drain in basket.
Repeat until all are fried. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: fried diced green tomatoes corn pones
directions: Layer #1:
Raw rice (not Minute rice).

title: cherry-coke salad
directions: Bring cherry juice to boil.
Dissolve Jell-O in cherry juice. Chop and pit cherries.
While still hot, crumble cream cheese. Add nuts, cherries and Coke.
Chill until firm.

title: rice and walnut roast
directions: Pour 3/4 cup milk over crumbs and let stand 5 minutes.
Saute onion and parsley until smooth.
Blend in milk/crumb mixture.
Add egg and walnuts; mix well.
Fold in rice and press gently into oiled loaf pan.
Bake 30 minutes (or until brown) at 350°.
Serve hot with favorite gravy and cranberry sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zesty chicken
directions: If using chicken, skin it.
Mix ingredients together.
Pour over the meat and bake at 350° until done.

title: turkey with a twist
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour and cook until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat. Combine salad dressing, turkey, noodles, peas, chiles, pepper and oregano. Stir in onion mixture.
Pour into shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Garnish top with tomato wedges, if desired. Serves 10.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Cut up chicken in serving size. Season with salt and pepper. Mix soy sauce, garlic, bourbon and oil.
Marinate for several hours.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes. Baste and turn often.

title: rhubarb cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs. Add buttermilk and vanilla. Measure all dry ingredients and mix together. Beat or stir in dry ingredients with the margarine and egg mixture. Chill dough. Roll out and cut into small cookies. Put spoonful of *rhubarb preserves on each and cover with another cookie. Press edges together and perforate top with fork before baking. Bake at 400° or 350° for approximately 10 minutes or until done.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix first 8 ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle on batter.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm.
Top with ice cream or Cool Whip.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: southern living swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 cup onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.
Good, good, good.

title: witches brew
directions: Pour ingredients in a clean gallon container.
Fill rest of container with tap water.
Stir and chill.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water; add grated (drained) cucumbers, onion, salt and vinegar.
Stir in green food coloring to desired color.
Pour in mold.

title: chewies
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar.
Add eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach-cheese pie(spanokopita)
directions: Cook chopped onions in	butter	until tender.
In bowl, beat eggs.
Add cheeses, dill,
mint,
cream of rice, salt and pepper; mix well.
Drain
chopped
spinach well.
Mix.
Add to the onion and cheese	mixture.
Spread filo, 3 layers, buttering each layer with
margarine.
Cut
into thirds.
Each makes one roll.
Spread spoonful of
filling on each piece and roll. Tuck ends in as you roll.
Bake
at
375° until browned, about 25 minutes.

title: ritz cracker salad
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in cracker crumbs, baking powder and sugar.
Bake in buttered 9 x 12-inch pan at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes, until crusty but not brown.
In hot water (on stove), add cream cheese and cherry Jell-O.
Blend, then add cherries.
Nuts are optional.
Spread over meringue layer.
Chill or freeze.

title: plain tea cake
directions: Roll thin and bake in a quick oven.
Flavor to taste.

title: classic pesto sauce
directions: Blanch nuts in boiling water to remove skins.
Blend all ingredients in blender or food processor until you have a smooth paste.
Place into a large warm bowl.
Cook pasta al dente.
Fork pasta directly from pot onto paste in bowl.
Toss well.
Add 2 tablespoons hot water from pot and toss again.
Serve in hot soup bowls.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix crumb and butter mixture.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat above mixture, eggs, oleo and sugar.
Spread over crust. Slice 4 bananas over this.
Drain and spread crushed pineapple over all.
Will not cover completely.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and decorate with half of maraschino cherry.
Refrigerate.
No bake.
Great cool dessert.

title: bread pudding with amaretto
directions: Break the bread up and soak it in milk in a bowl for 1 hour. Mix in 4 eggs, 2 cups sugar, raisins, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Blend 3/4 cup of sugar and butter in a saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in one egg.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Amaretto.
Spoon over warm bread pudding.

title: barbecue mochiko chicken
directions: Marinate chicken wings for 2 hours in a
mixture of the ingredients, except sesame seed.
Roll in
sesame
seed before frying in peanut oil.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix all well.
Pour into a greased pie plate.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned potato candy
directions: Peel skin off boiled potato and mash flat on counter.
Add enough powdered sugar to form a big flat "patty."
Roll out with rolling pin like pie dough.
Spread peanut butter over "patty" and roll up like a jelly-roll.
Cut into 1/2 pieces and let cool in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: low-fat dilly bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast in water;
stir.
Stir in 2 teaspoons of sugar; set aside.
Combine and mix the cottage cheese, onion, dill weed,
baking
powder, salt, sugar and Egg Beaters.
Add yeast and flour and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a
greased bowl.
Cover;
let
rise until doubled (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down
and knead a few times.
Divide and shape into
loaves. Place in 2 well-greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out on rack and cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, debone and put in bottom of baking dish (about 9 x 13-inch).
Pour cream of chicken soup over this.
Mix stuffing, egg, broth and onion.
Pour over chicken and soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: catfish chowder
directions: Cut fillets into 1-inch pieces.
Brown the bacon.
Add onion and saute.
Add water, potatoes, seasonings and fish.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add milk and heat.
Garnish with parsley and serve 6 lucky people.

title: mounds cake
directions: Prepare cake mix using package directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine milk, sugar, marshmallows and coconut in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until marshmallows are melted, stirring constantly.
Spread hot mixture over warm cake.

title: weight watcher's dessert
directions: Mix Rice Krispies and peanut butter to form crust in a pie pan.
Place sliced bananas on crust.
Make pudding according to directions on box.
Pour pudding over bananas.
Let set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Continue beating and add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture. Fold in nuts.
Put into greased and floured bread pans (2).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken curry
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Save two cups of chicken broth. Slice onion and saute in the shortening.
Add flour, curry, ginger, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Simmer until onions are soft.
Add chicken broth and chicken.
Cook one-half hour over medium heat.
Serve over rice.

title: antipasto shell salad
directions: Cook shells according to directions.
Mix salad dressing with oregano, salt and pepper.
Let sit.
Cut up meat and cheese.
Add to shells with olives, onion and chi chi beans.
Let sit overnight.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine melted Crisco, cocoa and salt, then add milk and vanilla.
Mix in sugar in 3 parts.	Mix until smooth and creamy. Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin if needed for good spreading consistency.
Frosts two 8 or 9-inch layers or a 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: wacky cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, sift all dry ingredients 3 times.
Level with fork.
Make 3 spoon wells in dry ingredients.
Put vinegar, oil and vanilla equally in wells.
Pour water over all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly with fork.
Do not beat!
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: marshmallow krispies
directions: Melt caramels, margarine and milk in double boiler.
Dip marshmallows in caramel mixture and roll in Rice Krispies.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and mix.
Add zucchini and mix.
Add all other ingredients and blend well.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix water, rice and mushroom soup.
Add onion soup mix.
Lay chicken breasts on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: broke da mouth stuffed aburage
directions: Mix ground pork, green onions, water chestnuts, 1/2 bottle oyster sauce, salt and pepper.
Stuff aburage and place in pot. Pour remaining oyster sauce over stuffed aburage; then pour chicken broth over and simmer for 30 minutes.
Check pork to make sure it's cooked.

title: ron's barbecue sauce
directions: Place in bowl and mix thoroughly.
This sauce can be used on any meat.

title: curried deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks; add mayonnaise and next 4 ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Spoon or pipe into egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish, if desired.

title: pickled squash
directions: Sprinkle squash and onion with salt.
Let stand 1 hour. Combine other ingredients. Bring to a boil. Add squash/onion mix. Bring to another boil. Remove from heat and put in jars.
Makes 7 pints.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice and save.
Cook flour, juice, egg and sugar until thick.
Stir in cream cheese.
Pour over pineapple, apples and pecans.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender. Drain well.
Mix together broccoli, soup, onion, eggs and milk.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Prepare stuffing according to directions.
Spoon cheese on broccoli.
Mix.
Top with stuffing.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: roast pork with six herbs
directions: Sprinkle roast with paprika; rub into surface. Combine herbs; rub over surface of roast. Place on rack in open roasting pan. Insert meat thermometer in center of roast. Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven 2 to 3 hours (allow about 30 minutes per pound) or until meat thermometer registers 165°. Remove from oven; let stand about 15 minutes (temperature will rise, reaching the recommended 170° and juices will set, making carving easier). Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: lemon squares
directions: Pour on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cut into squares.
Do not overmix crust or filling.
Use a fork and don't worry over lumps.

title: mama's waffles
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, margarine, flour and 1 cup milk.
Mix together until blended.
Add remaining milk.
May be used for pancakes also.

title: mom's banana bread
directions: Combine and mix in order given.
Bake in 1 large or 2 small pans at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook bacon crisp; crumble.
Combine 1/2 cup bacon drippings with next five ingredients.
Heat and stir until thickened.
Add potatoes, onion and bacon.
Toss; heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: oven french toast
directions: Slice bread in 1 1/2-inch thick slices and arrange in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, milk, sugar, salt and vanilla together.
Pour over bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Put a dash of butter on each slice and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with your favorite syrup. If desired, during the last 10 minutes of baking, put a smokie link on each slice.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with very bland crackers.

title: green beans supreme
directions: Place green beans in buttered baking dish.
Add onion and water chestnuts, then the mushroom soup.
Add margarine.
Sprinkle crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Cut cake into cubes.
Slice strawberries. Set aside (add a little sugar, if desired).
Mix together Cool Whip, sour cream, milk and powdered sugar.
Pour mixture over cake.
Mix.
Layer cake mixture, strawberries and glaze in a large container. Refrigerate.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and rice and mix well. Arrange chicken pieces in a large casserole dish and pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve over rice, separating gravy from chicken pieces, if desired.

title: beer barbecued bratwurst
directions: Boil bratwurst in large pan with water and 1 beer for about 1/2 hour.
Take out and put on the fire* or charcoal.
Stab with a fork to drain grease while cooking.
Serve on rolls with sauerkraut and mustard.
Fried potatoes go very well with this dish.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with oleo and press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and set aside.
Melt and cool chocolate and set aside. Cream butter and sugar, then add egg, melted chocolate and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, mixing after each addition.
Then mix in the coconut and nuts. Spoon dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets and bake for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire racks and cool.

title: orange pineapple sherbet
directions: Pour into ice cream freezer container and freeze.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together by hand.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Mix scalded milk, soft bread crumbs, cheese, butter and salt in mixing bowl.
Beat egg yolks until lemon colored; add the first mixture; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into battered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until set.
Makes 4 servings.
It's great with muffins for a meal.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and pour into pie shells. Sprinkle with reserved nuts and chill.
Cut into small wedges.

title: richmond frosting
directions: Mix
sugar
and
cornstarch. Add grated chocolate, salt and water.
Cook
until thick.	Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
While hot spread on cake.

title: honey wassail
directions: Mix juices and add cinnamon.
Bring to a boil and immediately remove from heat.
Stir in honey.
Serve hot.
Yield:
1 gallon and 1 3/4 quarts.

title: no-bake fudge cookies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Add sugar, milk, cocoa and salt.
Mix well. Bring just to the boiling point; do not boil. Remove from heat. Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats; mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Let stand until firm. Yields 3 dozen.

title: seven-layer lettuce salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Layer all ingredients in order listed.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours; overnight is better.
This salad is great for those summertime reunions.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Put ingredients into a blender and mix on high for 6 to 10 seconds.
Spoon into a dipping bowl and chill for at least 30 minutes.
Added spice:
Sprinkle paprika on top just before serving.
Sprinkle dill weed on top just before serving.
This is a great lo-cal dip that even tastes fattening.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mounds candy pieces
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, except paraffin wax and chocolate chips.
Pat to desired thickness on a greased (butter) cookie sheet.
Place in the refrigerator for several hours to chill.
Cut into small squares or rectangles.
In microwave oven in a large glass bowl, melt the paraffin wax, then add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Using a toothpick, dip bars of coconut into the chocolate mixture and place onto wax paper to set.
You may place in the refrigerator to cool.
If the melted wax and chocolate chips mixture becomes thick, you may put back into the microwave for a few seconds to make thinner.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake in an 11 x 13-inch dish as directed on box.
Let cake cool 10 minutes and then poke holes in it with the end of a wooden spoon.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake and let run into the holes.
Pour caramel topping over the sweetened condensed milk. Spread Cool Whip over the top and sprinkle with crushed Heath bars. Store in refrigerator.
Delicious!

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually, beating until well blended. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add egg yolks.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture.
Stir in vanilla and jam.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 15 minutes, then at 360° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: beverly evanson's impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream if desired.

title: spumoni
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Beat just until soft peaks form.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Cover.
Freeze firm (4 hours).
Will fill an 8 x 8-inch pan or two purchased crumb crusts.

title: dressing balls
directions: Heat fat in skillet.
Saute onion, celery and parsley.
Add bread crumbs and seasonings.
Stir to blend well.
Add eggs, slightly beaten, and enough stock to make crumbs hold together.

title: great sugar cookies
directions: Mix well the shortening, sugar, eggs and extract.
Blend flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut with 3-inch cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place 1 or 2 raisins in center of cookie.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.

title: freezer okra
directions: Wash and slice the tender okra.
Coat with Crisco oil.
Cover okra with cornmeal.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Bag when cool; freeze.

title: sesame baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in margarine.
Combine all other ingredients except seeds.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: clams casino
directions: Combine all ingredients in small frying pan.
Cook at 350° until tender.
Add bread crumbs.
Put into clam shells; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: elsie's pancake syrup
directions: Dissolve sugar in water and add flavoring.
Pour over pancakes, waffles or French toast.

title: poor man's crab cakes
directions: Mix well; shape into thin patties.
Fry until brown on both sides in a small amount of fat.
Steam a little to be sure they are done.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
When done, let rest in pan 5 minutes.
Have mixed together juice of 1 lemon, 1/2 cup sugar and little of rind.
Have this mixed while bread is cooking, then pour over bread.
Use spoon to cover with lemon juice.
Cool.
Wrap in wax paper and foil.

title: burger skillet delite
directions: Soak onion in
milk
for
5 minutes.
Mix in beef, egg, oatmeal, salt and
pepper.	Put
in 10-inch Dutch oven.
Brush top with
Kitchen Bouquet.
Combine spaghetti sauce and beans. Pour over meat mixture.	Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: raisin brown bread(makes 5 loaves)
directions: In saucepan, bring raisins, soda and water to a boil; when forms, remove from heat.
Mix eggs, vanilla, sugar and salt and add to raisins alternately with flour.
Add nuts.
Bake in 5 (No. 2) cans.
Grease and flour cans.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Fill cans half full.

title: shrimp mosca
directions: Heat oil in frypan.
Add shrimp and spices.
Saute for 15 to 20 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.
Add wine and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes more. Shrimp are to be peeled at table and served with hot crisp bread for dunking into sauce.
Serves 2.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
With fork, beat eggs slightly.
Mix in meat, crumbs, onions and salt.
Combine other ingredients.
The secret is to mix well, but lightly.
Do not pack in baking dish. Shape meat into a loaf .
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: joyce's peanut bars
directions: Mix until crumbly, flour, sugar, salt and 1/2 cup butter. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: quick, easy -n- fast snickers salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Serve within a few hours.

title: mexi-rice chicken
directions: Fry bacon in medium skillet, remove from pan and crumble. Brown chicken in bacon fat for 5 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken from skillet and dispose of fat.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Dilute cream of chicken soup and milk.
Combine mixture and cooked ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with seasoned crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve hot.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Separate the eggs.
Beat yolks and add to sugar mixture.
Slowly add milk and mix well.
Cook until it thickens, stirring all the time.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell. Prepare meringue and spread on pie.
Bake until meringue is lightly browned.

title: peppermint almond bark swirls
directions: Crush peppermint.
Microwave almond bark until able to stir creamy smooth.
Mix peppermint and almond bark.
Pour into square nonstick sprayed or buttered casserole dish.
If desired drop a few drops of food coloring and a few chocolate chips on top of mixture.
Swirl with a fork until color swirls in the mixture. Let cool.
Break with a knife into pieces.
(Red makes a beautiful Christmas candy.)

title: pizza sandwich
directions: Cook ground beef until brown; drain.
Mix in 1 can tomato sauce and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir baking mix, egg and milk to make a soft dough.
Spread half of the dough into greased oblong pan.
Pour remaining can of tomato sauce over dough.
Layer 6 slices cheese, meat, mushrooms and remaining cheese.
Cover with remaining dough.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400° or until brown.

title: pepper slaw
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar, pepper, salt and celery seed. Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Keep chilled.
Grind or use blender for vegetables.

title: food processor pie crust
directions: Place small pieces of Crisco on a plate and put in the freezer.
When frozen, place flour and salt in food processor bowl with the big blade and add Crisco.
Process for 8 seconds on high. Add water and process for 8 seconds on high or until it forms a ball.
Makes two 9-inch pie crusts.

title: company chicken
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer dried beef, overlapping.
Place chicken on top, placing bacon on top of chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until chicken pulls away from edge of pan.
Drain excess juice out of pan.
In bowl, combine mushroom soup and sour cream together, then cover chicken with it (like you would frost a cake).
Return to oven and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Chicken breasts may be substituted with other parts of chicken, just debone and remove skin.

title: sugar-free glazed strawberry pie
directions: Crush 2 cups berries into pan; add 3/4 cup white grape juice. Bring to boil; reduce heat, simmer 2 minutes.
Sieve out pulp. Return 1 1/4 cups of liquid to the pan.
In separate container, combine 1/4 cup white grape juice and the cornstarch.
Add this to the liquid in the pan.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Then cook 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in the sweetener and coloring.
Spread 1/4 of this mixture over pie crust.
Then layer berries and mixture over this.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Serve topped with dairy whip.
Makes 8 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking soda and powder together and set aside.
Blend eggs, softened butter, sugar and bananas.
Add blended mixture to the dry ingredients and mix just until moistened (do not beat).
Stir in chopped nuts.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before turning out.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip, butter and sugar. Set aside. Mix together pudding mixes, vanilla and milk. Add it to cream cheese mixture. Crush package of Oreo cookies in blender until they are crumbs. Put 1/2 of crumbs in deep dish. Pour the filling over crumbs. Top with the rest of the crumbs. Store in refrigerator.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pan.
Stir well until crackers are well coated.
Bake on large cookie sheet in 200° oven for about an hour, stirring occasionally.

title: kathy's quiche
directions: *May substitute Egg Beaters or similar product

title: vermont apple cinnamon bread
directions: Grate apples and stir in soda.
Combine with remaining ingredients and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Pour into greased bread pan, 5 x 8 1/2-inches.

title: white bean bruschetta
directions: Heat beans in a small saucepan, over medium heat, until boiling.
Place beans in a small bowl; mash with lemon juice, garlic and basil.
Spread on bread.
Drizzle on olive oil and sprinkle with cheese and black pepper.
Makes 1 serving.

title: c p d hash browns
directions: Can use part package of onion soup mix instead of onions and peppers.

title: momma's plain cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix flour in and then add milk.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until done.

title: chicken biscuit stew dinner
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In ovenproof skillet, melt margarine. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add chicken, onion, peas and carrots.
Simmer until hot and bubbly.
Separate dough and arrange over chicken mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: four bean salad
directions: Mix beans together in a bowl.
Place onion and green pepper slices on top of beans.
Combine vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper; pour over beans.
Let stand overnight.

title: lady baltimore cake(mom's)
directions: Sift some cake flour 3 times, then measure 3 cups flour, then sift it again with the baking powder. Sift the sugar.
Cream the sugar with the butter until smooth and creamy.
Measure out the milk. Add some of the flour to the sugar mixture and alternate with the milk until all have been added.
Beat the egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Add to cake mix and fold in.
Bake in 3 layer pans that have been lightly greased and floured.
Bake for about 1/2 hour or until done in preheated 325° oven.
Frost with 7 Minute Icing.

title: taco meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine first eight ingredients.
Add beef; mix well.
Press into a greased 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pan.
Bake uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1-1/2 hours or until meat thermometer read 160°.
Serve with salsa, sour cream, cheese, and additional olives if desired.

title: baked pumpkin pie(serve with low-fat whipped topping)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and cloves.
Stir in pumpkin.
Add vanilla, evaporated milk, orange rind and egg whites.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into the pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 325°. Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: mexican delight
directions: Layer refried beans and Cheddar cheese.
Mix cornmeal, buttermilk and egg and pour over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: hungarian cream cheese crescents
directions: Mix flour, cream cheese and margarine thoroughly.
Form into a ball.
Refrigerate overnight in a bowl covered with waxed paper. Roll out dough a half or quarter at a time on a board covered with powdered sugar.
Use a pastry cutter to cut into approximately a 2-inch square or desired size.
Place small amount of filling in center and fold as desired.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: thimble cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and blend well.
Roll into balls the size of a small walnut.
Roll each ball in unbeaten egg white and then in finely chopped nutmeats.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Remove cookie sheet from oven and make small depression in center of each cookie (use thimble).
Fill hole with jelly.
Return to oven and bake for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: sausage and squash bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Halve and seed squash; place cut side down in shallow
baking
pan.
Add	1/2-inch water to pan and bake 35 to
minutes	or
until
tender.
Brown sausage well;
pour off
drippings.
Stir
in
celery,	onion,	green pepper, Provolone and
Parmesan
cheese.
Turn squash cut side up; dot with butter.
Salt and pepper insides of squash.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 15 additional minutes.

title: paul neuman's chocolate cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake as directed in 9 X 13 pan. Remove from oven and poke holes in top with handle of wooden spoon. Pour sweetened condensed milk over the top of the entire cake. Then pour topping over that. Cool completely. Cover with a thick layer of cool whip. Crush Heath bars into pieces and sprinkle over top. Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate nut bark(microwave)
directions: Place
chocolate
chips
in a microwavesafe dish; cover with plastic wrap
and microwave at Medium (5) 6 minutes. Stir in 1 cup
whole	toasted
almonds.
Spread
thinly over waxed paper covered
cardboard	or
cookie sheet.
Chill until firm. Break into pieces.

title: elias pafford's bear hash(his specialty in the cold winter)
directions: Place all meat stew in 6-quart boiler.
Cook until it falls to pieces, then add onions and potatoes and cook until tender.
Add all vegetables; simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve with cornbread or saltine crackers.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in shortening until onion is transparent.
Add hamburger, salt and pepper.
Cook until meat is lightly browned.
Remove from heat and drain.
Arrange layers of meat mixture and macaroni in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup with water.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Pour mixture over meat and macaroni.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put crust on bottom of pie plate. Mix Veg-All, cream of chicken soup and 2 boiled chicken breasts. Place in pie crust and put other pie crust on top. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: rice and broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine 1/2 stick of butter, rice, broccoli, Cheez Whiz, soup and onions in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Dot the top with remaining 1/2 stick of butter and cook for 30 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites, gradually adding sugar - form soft peaks. Mix in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon full on foil or brown paper.
Put in 375° oven immediately and turn off.
Leave for two hours or overnight.

title: dill pickles
directions: Sterilize jars. Cut up and pack cukes in jars. Add first five items to each jar of cukes.

title: almond cookies
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and extract, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Flatten slightly.
Brush with egg white.
Place sliced almonds on center of each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: chili con queso
directions: Cube cheese.
Put in crock-pot or double boiler.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir often.
Serve with chips.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Use your own judgement on bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: southwest dip
directions: After broccoli is cooked and drained, set aside.
Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add all other ingredients and broccoli.
Heat over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: seasoned stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels.
Remove mushroom stems and finely chop; set caps aside.
Combine mushroom stems and remaining ingredients, stirring well; spoon into mushroom caps. Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Place butter in a large glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on High for 45 seconds to 1 minute or until melted.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in dry ingredients just until blended.
Fold in nuts.
Spread evenly into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square baking dish.
Microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 8 to 10 minutes or until top appears dry and springs back when lightly touched.
Turn dish 1/2 turn halfway through cooking.
Allow to stand on a solid surface until completely cool.
Cut into bars. Yields 16 brownies.

title: rotini salad
directions: Prepare rotini as package directs.
Drain well.
Add next 5 ingredients in small bowl.
Blend oil, lemon juice, soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Toss with rotini mixture.
Chill.
Garnish. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate potato cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Beat in eggs.
Add potatoes.
Beat good.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Pour in a greased tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in a saucepan.
Cook for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add marshmallow creme, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well. Pour into greased dish.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
5 pounds.

title: mary's yeast rolls
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Add enough flour to make consistency of biscuit dough (about 3 1/2 quarts).
Put in a bowl and brush with butter.
Let rise until it doubles in size.
Punch down.
Pinch off into rolls.
Brush with butter and let rise again until it doubles in size, then bake.
Brush with butter when done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except eggs.
Put half of the meat in a meat loaf pan.
Lay eggs on top of meat in a row.
Place remainder of meat on top.
Lay strips of bacon on top.
Bake in 375° oven for one and a half hours.

title: wild rice chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
While rice is cooking, melt butter and saute onion.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in half and half and broth.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add water to drained juice to make 2 cups of liquid; bring to a boil.
Stir in Jell-O and cranberry sauce.
Refrigerate until slightly congealed.

title: chip dip
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix at high speed until well blended.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix first 6 items (leave raw).
Boil chicken or shrimp with water and salad dressing mix.
Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: party punch base
directions: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Strain and discard spices. Chill.
Combine with apple juice, apricot nectar and lemon or lime juice.
Makes 5 cups base.

title: giza cheese cake
directions: Combine ingredients thoroughly and reserve 2 tablespoons. Press mixture firmly against the bottom and sides of a 10-inch tube pan.
Pour in filling and sprinkle with reserved graham cracker mixture.

title: tomato souffle
directions: Cook in boiler the first 3 items until thick.
Pour over bread slices arranged in a baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or 300° until bubbly and thick.

title: enchiladas con pollo(chicken)
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Combine
half
of
cheese
with chicken, tomatoes, olives, chilies and onion.
Mix well with 1 cup taco
sauce.
Dip
each tortilla in remaining taco sauce. Top with
cup of the filling, roll up and place seam side down in
a
buttered
13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread remaining taco sauce over
tortillas.
Cover
with foil and bake 30 minutes. Remove foil
and
sprinkle
with remaining cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: crab meat appetizer
directions: Blend cream cheese, butter and onion.
Fold in crab meat.
Cut muffins into fourths.
Spread topping on each piece of muffin. Place under broiler for five minutes.
Serve hot.

title: georgia pound cake
directions: Beat butter well; add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla and lemon or almond extract.
Add confectioners sugar. Add flour; beat well.
Bake in ungreased tube cake pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken wings
directions: Marinate chicken wings overnight in wet ingredients (sugar, ginger, soy sauce, water and garlic salt combined).
Bake at 400° on cookie sheets covered with aluminum foil for 20 minutes.
Turn wings over.
Bake another 20 to 25 minutes.
Keep warm in crock-pot to serve at a party.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup of the cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can of the onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered for 5 minutes longer.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Brown margarine or butter lightly.
Stir in bread and cracker crumbs.
Put thin layer in the bottom of a shallow buttered dish. Cover with oysters and add salt and pepper.
Then add half each of the liquor or cream.
Repeat the oyster and crumb layers, but not more than 2 layers.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: christmas ribbon jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until set.

title: the victorian tea room's squash casserole
directions: Slice the squash and chop the onion; simmer them together with a little water until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.

Drain excess water and stir in the other ingredients, reserving 1/4 cup of cheese. Pour the mixture into a greased casserole; sprinkle with the reserved cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until firm. Serves 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet; stir in flour and add rest of ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Let set for 5 minutes before serving.
Bake in 8-inch wide or 2 to 3 deep pans.

title: carrot cake
directions: Thoroughly mix ingredients, except carrots. Fold in carrots. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Use Bundt pan, lightly greased and floured.

title: banana nut bread(1 loaf)
directions: Cream margarine and add sugar, eggs, salt, soda, vanilla and bananas.
Mix well.
Add flour a little at a time until all mixed. Add nuts and mix again.
Sprinkle brown sugar over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check earlier if you have an extra hot oven.

title: shrimp and cheese ball
directions: Defrost shrimp and rinse.
Mix shrimp and all ingredients well and form into a ball.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Stir lemon juice in milk.
Add other ingredients and pour into baked graham cracker shell.
This makes two 9-inch pies.
Chill, but is better frozen to serve.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Saute onions in oleo, add soup and 1 can water.
Add broccoli, cheese and cooked rice.
Mix thoroughly. Put in casserole dish, sprinkle with paprika and bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
Mix with margarine.
Add well beaten egg yolks, milk and coconut.
Pour in uncooked pastry shell and bake at 350° until almost firm.
Beat 3 egg whites until almost stiff; then add 4 tablespoons sugar (1 at a time), while continuing to beat.
Spread on pie and brown in oven at 325°.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Remove the stems from the mushrooms, chop finely and saute in the butter about 6-8 minutes until tender. Stir together the bread crumbs, soup mix, almonds and cheese. Stuff the mushroom caps and bake in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan, uncovered, at 425° for 12-15 minutes.

title: cukes
directions: Cut cukes into long thin strips.
Bring water, salt, sugar and vinegar to a boil; cool.
Pack cukes into 2 half gallon or 1 gallon jug.
Pour mixture over cukes and add 1 clove garlic and fresh dill.
Put in refrigerator and don't use for 24 hours.
Always keep refrigerated.
You may use quart jars if you wish.
It will make 2 to 3 quart jars.

title: chili
directions: Cover ground chuck or round in water in large container and simmer until red is out.
Add all other ingredients and water if needed to keep this consistency so chili will not be too thick.

title: payday
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix yellow cake mix with egg.
Melt 1/3 cup margarine into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press cake mix/egg mixture into the pan.
Bake for 12 to 18 minutes.
When cake is still hot, spread miniature marshmallows on top.

title: chicken napoli
directions: In a skillet over medium-high heat in hot olive oil, cook chicken until golden brown.
Remove thighs to plate as soon as they brown.
Drain fat from skillet.
In the same skillet, add marinara sauce, sugar and salt, stirring to remove brown bits from bottom of pan.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and cook chicken until it is fork-tender, about 20 minutes turning meat once.

title: great northern beans
directions: Cook beans until done. Add brown sugar and mustard a little at a time, to your taste. Add tomatoes and cook until hot.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar and butter and spread over top of batter.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage cheese biscuits
directions: Fry sausage, crumble, and pat dry on paper towels.
Add sausage and cheese to dry bisquick.
Mix together.
Add spices and milk. Roll in balls.
Bake at 400 degrees for approximately 10 minutes.

title: watergate pudding
directions: Mix the Cool Whip with the pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine all
ingredients, except soda and popcorn, in 2 quart dish.
Bring to a boil and then cook on full power for 2 minutes. Remove
from microwave and stir in soda.
Put popped corn in brown
grocery
bag.
Pour	syrup
mixture over corn, close bag and
shake.
Cook
in
bag	on
full power for 1 1/2 minutes. Shake and
cook
another 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour onto a cookie sheet and cool.

title: raisin graham muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in crushed crackers and raisins.
In another bowl, stir together dry ingredients and add to egg mixture, stirring just until moistened.

title: ham roll-up
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Place slice of Swiss cheese on top of ham slice, top with broccoli and roll up.
Place cut side down in greased baking dish.
Cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and margarine together and pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Beat 5 eggs until thoroughly mixed.
Add syrup, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat together and add pecans.
Pour on the crust and reduce heat in oven to 275° and bake for 50 minutes.

title: picnic potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until soft; drain and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and stir together.
This is better if prepared a day in advance and refrigerated overnight.

title: range top stuffing
directions: Saute onion in margarine in large skillet until tender.
Stir in all other ingredients, except broth.
Heat, stirring constantly, until bread cubes are slightly toasted.
Then, stir in enough broth to moisten mixture slightly, but not soggy!
Heat, tossing lightly until hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Cook broccoli and drain. Add to other ingredients and pour in casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake until bubbles like macaroni and cheese at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german hot red slaw
directions: Shred and core cabbage, then boil with bay leaf, onion, sugar and salt.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vinegar and apples.
Garnish with bacon bits.

title: cheese sausage muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs and milk; add to sausage mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pan 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut dessert sauce
directions: Spread	peanuts
on
a	large
glass pizza plate or pie plate. Microwave	at
High
for
minutes or until nuts are lightly toasted, stirring at 2 minute intervals.
Let stand 5 minutes, stirring every minute; set aside.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Select fresh green broccoli and cut away or peel tough stalks. Freshen in cold water for 1 hour.
Dice or slice tender stalks and break flowerets into small bits.
Add other ingredients and toss.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse and dry mushrooms.
Remove stems.
Chop stems and any caps that are broken.
Saute onions in butter.
Add chopped mushrooms and pieces.
Cook until soft.
Add cream and salt and pepper to taste.
Add Stove Top stuffing from the box.
Add about 1/2 of the box, more or less depending on the size of the mushrooms.
Cook until thick.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan; set aside. Cream butter and cream cheese. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour and salt, stirring until combined. Stir in vanilla and remaining 1 cup pecans. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely on a rack.

title: christmas bonbons
directions: Combine milk, powdered sugar and oleo.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Add coconut, walnuts and cherries; mix thoroughly.
Chill 1 hour.
Form into small balls.
Chill another 2 hours.
Melt chocolate.
Dip individually into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to cool.
Chill in refrigerator.
Makes about 150 pieces.

title: queen elizabeth's cake
directions: Sprinkle soda over dates.
Pour boiling water over dates and soda.
Add margarine.
Stir and let cool.
Add egg.
Sift together flour, sugar and salt; add to date mixture.
Stir in pecans or walnuts.
Bake in greased pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball-dried beef
directions: Mix together cream cheese, onion, salt and Accent.
Add 2/3 chopped beef.
Shape into ball.
Press remaining beef on outside of ball.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust according to package directions for two-crust pie, using 9-inch pie pan.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove bones.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup and water and pour over chicken.
Add broth to stuffing mix.
Spoon over chicken and soup.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix beef, crumbs, 1/2 of the Velveeta (cubed), egg, onion and pepper.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Melt the remaining cheese with 2 teaspoons milk and pour over meat loaf before serving.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Layer scrambled eggs, mushrooms, cheese and soup.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, onion and salt and refrigerate for several hours.
Meanwhile, cook the cup of macaroni rings.
After sitting time, add grapes, oranges, celery, almonds and macaroni to chicken mixture.
Then, add salad dressing.
Mix and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Then, fold in whipped cream before serving.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: In a pan, mix and bring to a boil; cook 5 minutes.
Leave cake in pan and punch holes in it with handle of wooden spoon.
Pour icing over cake and let stand for 2 hours.

title: baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken breast or cut up chicken in 1/2 cup Pet milk. Coat chicken in mixture of flour, pepper and salt. Melt oleo in casserole. Place coated chicken in pan and put in 425° oven for 30 minutes. Turn the chicken and pour over it the soup, water and remaining Pet milk. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: very delicious dip!
directions: Hollow out top of bread loaf.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese, grated Cheddar cheese, chiles and onions.
Put in loaf.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Place tomato slices in a serving bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over tomatoes.
Allow to marinate 1 hour or longer.

title: sweet and sour delight
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch pieces.
Brown in oil in pan.
Reduce heat to low, add onion and garlic.
Cover, cook for 10 minutes. Add carrots and green pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients. Stir into skillet.
Cover, simmer 10 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: yellow squash pickles
directions: Cover squash, onions and peppers with cold water that has 2 Tbsp. salt (pickling) added to it. Let stand for 2 hours, then drain off water.
Make a syrup of vinegar and sugar.
Put mustard see and celery seed in a cheese cloth and put with syrup mixture. Boil mixture then add drained squash, onions, and peppers.
Bring to a boil again and cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Mix together boiling water, margarine, baking soda and raisins. Let stand 3 hours.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and divide evenly in three 1 pound coffee cans which have been sprayed with Pam or well-greased.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Crush cornflakes.
Mix all ingredients until blended.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Divide into 1-inch balls.
Press flat and place on greased cookie trays.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown.
They bake very quickly, depends on individual oven and thickness of tray and cheese.

title: old-fashioned potato salad(begin early in the day)
directions: In a large bowl, stir mayonnaise with next 5 ingredients until mixed; add remaining ingredients except lettuce and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Contains 410 calories per serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle Pepperidge Farm Stuffing on top. Bake in preheated oven at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: koulouria(greek easter cookies)
directions: Cream butter and add sugar; mix thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs and continue mixing.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Knead dough well and shape as desired.
Dip in sesame seed and bake at 350°, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter special k bars
directions: In a large sauce pan bring sugar and syrup to boiling.

title: m.p.h. roast beef
directions: Sprinkle onion soup and water over meat.
Lay roast on 2 to 3 layers of heavy-duty foil.
Add whole carrots and whole potatoes. Add mushroom soup.
Fold up foil to close.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix sugars and shortening after creaming; add eggs and beat. Add dry ingredients and mix throughly.
Stir chocolate chips, oatmeal and bran.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: braunschweiger cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Combine braunschweiger, 1 package cream cheese, onion and half of bacon bits.
Mix thoroughly and form into ball.
Beat remaining package of cream cheese until fluffy, spread over outside of braunschweiger ball.
Cover completely and sprinkle with remaining bacon bits.
Chill.

title: special fried rice
directions: Heat wok to medium-high.
Add 1 teaspoon oil.
Whisk eggs and add to wok until omelette is formed.
Flip (in 2 minutes). Remove omelette and chop into bite size chunks.
Save in large bowl.

title: lottie's fried corn bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then add rest of ingredients.
It makes about 3 cups.
Put 3/4 inch grease in large frypan.
Spoon mixture into grease (hot).
Turn when light brown. When light brown on both sides, it is done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place oleo and peanut butter in saucepan.
Heat and stir until all melts together smooth.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in powdered sugar.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all together real well.

title: strawberry fig jam
directions: Combine mashed figs, sugar and jello and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Slowly bring to a boil and boil slowly for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into jars and process in water bath for 10 minutes.
Can be mixed and stored in refrigerator overnight.

title: easy beef pot pie
directions: Place beef, beef broth, vinegar and onion into a crock-pot. Cook until tender.
Separate meat from juice.
Place meat into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix in vegetables with the meat.
Pour juice into saucepan and bring to a boil.
Put flour and 2 cups milk into jar and shake until well blended.
Add mix to beef juice and stir until it returns to a boil, then add mushroom soup and stir until well blended.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat shortening and sugar until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies. Bake 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack and let cool completely.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs; alternate milk and flour.
Blend well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rolls
directions: Mix together.
Add flour to consistency.
Let dough rise once; knead down.
Let rise second time; roll out and cut with glass. Place in pan.
Let rise again and bake at 375° until done.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt separately.
Slowly add flour mixture to sugar mixture; blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: ranch chicken
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Line 13 x 9 pan with taco shells.

title: aunt helen's squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook sliced squash and onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain squash.
Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in shredded carrots.
Fold in squash and onions.
Combine stuffing mix and butter or margarine.
Spread half of stuffing mix in bottom, 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable over stuffing.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over vegetable.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Cut each pack of rolls to make 2 layers (top and bottom). Place a layer of ham slices on bottom layer of rolls, then a layer of cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Heat 2 to 3 minutes in microwave until watery.
Stir well.
Pour 1/2 mixture over bottom layers.
Place top layer of rolls on top, then pour remaining butter sauce on the top layer.
(You will be doing both layers at the same time.)
Place rolls in oven on 350° until cheese is thoroughly melted, then cut into small pieces.
I make a double recipe of the butter sauce for a more zesty flavor.

title: eight bean soup mix
directions: Measure 1 1/2 cups of bean mixture and 1 tablespoon of salt. Wash and soak bean mixture with 1 tablespoon of salt for 3 hours. Drain.
Add ham bone or 1 1/2 pounds of ham scraps.
Boil for 3 hours or until tender in 3 quarts of water.
Add 1 (No. 2) can tomatoes, 1 large chopped onion, one (4 ounce) can chopped green chilies and 1 clove of crushed garlic.
Add salt and Tabasco sauce to taste.
Add 1 bay leaf and juice of 1 lemon.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: herbed chicken casserole
directions: Stew and debone chicken.
Tear into pieces.
Reserve 2 cups broth.
Place chicken pieces in bottom of greased 3 quart dish. Combine soup and 1 cup broth and pour over chicken.
Mix butter, remaining broth, celery, onion, stuffing and pepper.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown. Serves 8 to 10.

title: garlic butter sauce
directions: Beat the butter until fluffy.
Stir in the snipped parsley and garlic.
Refrigerate.
Bring to room temperature before serving. Yields 1/2 cup.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, onion, salt, pepper, egg and bread crumbs together. Form into a loaf.
Place in pan.
Pour tomato sauce over loaf and water around it.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: salmon and rice balls
directions: Combine salmon, rice, onions, bread crumbs, eggs, garlic powder, thyme, red pepper and salt.
Form into balls.
Add green pepper, celery, garlic and tomato sauce.
Pour into baking dish. Drop salmon balls into sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot rhubarb.
Allow to cool.
Add crushed pineapple, juice and all.
Add the nuts.
Refrigerate until set. Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: chicken and macaroni casserole
directions: Mix everything together and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.
Take out one hour ahead of cooking time.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered. If you don't have 4 hours to let it set, cook the macaroni in the 2 cups broth first, then mix everything together and put it directly in the oven.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 1/2 x 15-inch baking pan (jelly roll type with sides; I used a 9 x 13-inch pan).
In a saucepan over high heat, bring water and margarine to a boil. Reduce heat.
Stir in flour until mixture forms a ball. Remove from heat.
By hand, beat in eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each addition until mixture is smooth. Spread mixture evenly over bottom of prepared pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
(Surface of pastry will be uneven.) Cool completely in pan on wire rack.

title: lobster
directions: Cut lobster
straight
down the middle through the tail. Clean the intestines out
and
put the bread crumbs until it is completely filled.
Slice the butter
and
stick butter down in the bread crumbs.
If desired,
put
garlic
powder
before the bread crumbs.
Cook in the 350° oven for 20 minutes.
(Melt the other butter to dip the lobster in when done.)

title: chicken broccoli braid
directions: Mix all ingredients. Unroll 1 pkg of rolls.Do not separate. Roll on cookie sheet to full size. Split along sides 3 inches and 1 1/2 inches apart. Spread filling down center. Left strips across mixture to meet in center. Twist strips, fold down. Bake at 275° until brown. Makes 2 braids.

title: frittata with broccoli and potatoes(4 servings)
directions: In a large covered nonstick ovenproof skillet, cook potatoes in oil over medium heat, stirring once or twice, for about 10 minutes or until tender and lightly browned.

title: corn and sausage bake
directions: Combine corn, green pepper and onion.
Place half the mixture in bottom of a 10 x 6 x 2-inch buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 the crackers over the corn and add the remaining corn. Sprinkle the remaining crackers over the corn mix.
Mix the milk, salt and pepper and pour over the corn mix.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Brown the sausage links and serve on top of the baked corn.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Roll roast in flour.
Cover bottom of skillet with oil.
Brown roast on all sides.
Remove roast from skillet; sprinkle more flour into drippings left in skillet.
Stir in enough water to make a very thick gravy.
Pour gravy into bottom of crock-pot.
Place roast on top of gravy.
Insert onion slices between sides of roast.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: cheesy corn custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place casserole in pan of hot water and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until custard is set.
Serves four.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Place in saucepan with 1/4 cup butter; heat until melted, stirring often.
Place vegetables in 1-quart dish.
Pour cheese over mixture; mix well.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients, reserving noodles and butter.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Cover with noodles.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Recipe may be frozen.
Thaw at room temperature 1 hour before serving.

title: cheesy beef boats
directions: In skillet, brown beef, mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Add tomato sauce, basil, oregano, salt and pepper; lower heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Hollow out rolls, leaving 1/2-inch shell. Fill rolls with meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over meat mixture. Place on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix orange juice with water as per directions.
Add cranberry juice and chill.
Add club soda just before serving.

title: dandy cake
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients into a saucepan and bring to a boil.
When cold, add the rest of the ingredients.
If desired, can add meats, citron, currants, etc.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use a butter frosting.

title: hi-hat salads
directions: Place 1 slice of pineapple on each lettuce leaf.
Spread each slice of pineapple with cottage cheese.
Add a thick sliced of jellied cranberry sauce.
Top with a dollop of cottage cheese in the center.

title: boneless beef chuck pot roast
directions: In large, heavy pan, brown meat in shortening.
Pour off fat. Stir in soup and 3/4 cup water.
Cover; cook over low heat for 3 hours, or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Remove roast to serving plate.
Skim excess fat from pan juices.
Blend 1/4 cup water with flour until smooth.
Slowly stir into meat sauce. Cook; stir until thickened.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mock mince pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Cover with top crust.
Bake in hot oven at 435° for about 25 minutes.

title: easy grape-nuts pudding
directions: Beat everything together and pour into a sprayed casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain off fat.
In a casserole dish, slice the potatoes, using a layer of potatoes, layer of onion. Pour 1/2 of both cans of soup over the potatoes and onion.
Cook until potatoes begin to soften when a fork is inserted. Take out of oven, mixing other half of both soups, flour, salt and pepper. Stir real good.
Add ground beef to potatoes and onion, pouring flour soup over potatoes.
Top with cheese. Return back to oven about 15 minutes at 300° or until soup thickens.

title: squash and broccoli casserole
directions: Combine squash, broccoli, onion, carrot, salt and water in saucepan.
Cook, covered, until vegetables are tender; drain.
Add margarine, sour cream and soup; mix well.
Stir in 1 cup stuffing mix and 1 cup cheese.
Spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Top with remaining stuffing mix and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cook cleaned peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Mix all other ingredients, except 1/2 cup soup.
Stuff peppers. Stand peppers upright in a shallow baking dish.
Pour over remaining soup, mixed with 1/2 cup water.
Bake covered 45 minutes, uncovered, for 15 additional minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until brown.

title: can't be cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk separately and pour onto butter.
Pour 1 can of pie filling onto batter mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° until brown (45 minutes).
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Mix together the first five ingredients.
Divide into three equal parts and freeze each part in a 1 gallon Ziploc bag.
When ready to serve, add 1 bottle of Sprite to each bag of the frozen punch base. (Remove bags from the freezer in time to get mushy.) This will serve 60 to 70 people.
The base will last in the freezer a long time.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Beat shortening and margarine until creamy.
Add powdered sugar and beat until creamy.
In separate bowl, beat pudding and milk until thick.
Then add pudding mix to first bowl and beat until creamy.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Have butcher bone chicken breasts.
Remove skin and cut meat into 10 or 12 strips.
Melt butter in skillet over high heat.
Add chicken.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and tarragon.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth and lemon slices. Lower heat, cover and cook 3 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serve with hot, cooked rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 batter in oblong pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon over batter and swirl with a knife.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Butter a small casserole dish. Mix flour and sugar. Add pineapple and cheese.
Top with coarsely crushed crackers and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepperoni pizza snacks
directions: Place muffins on baking sheet.
Spread with pizza sauce.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until bubbly.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in oregano and garlic powder.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Dip pieces into melted mixture.
Place pieces into a slightly greased tube pan.
Place pieces evenly around pan on top of one another.
Bake biscuits according to label.
Usually 325° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Place serving dish on top of tube pan and invert bread.
Pieces pull away easily.
Serve warm.
Can be used for breakfast by using 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon instead of oregano and garlic.

title: grit patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Lightly oil a pan and make small patties and fry them until brown.

title: little cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and brown sugar. Add the milk, graham crackers, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop into small papers. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Do not overbake.
Frost with the melted Hershey candy bar.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Refrigerate. It is best when served cold.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In casserole or pan with tight fitting lid, layer bread, cabbage, onions and garlic.
Spoon in tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour stock into pan carefully so as not to disturb layers.
Cook covered over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Serves 6.

title: fruit punch
directions: Make up Kool-Aid with sugar and water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Serves 50 to 60 people.

title: marinade for meats
directions: Mix together. Pour marinade into a nonmetal container. Place meat in marinade; turn several times. Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 days.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Fold or stir in egg whites.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: cajun soup
directions: You may substitute beef broth and 1 can (6 ounces) tomato sauce in place of whole tomatoes and chicken broth.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Simmer 25 minutes all the ingredients in a covered saucepan. Strain and sweeten to taste.
(I use 1 1/2 cups sugar.)

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Place sauteed chicken, peppers and onions in middle of tortilla.
Roll up; secure with toothpick.
Warm 30 seconds in microwave or a few minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with salsa, sour cream and shredded cheese on the side, as desired.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Bake at 375° in a 9-inch pan.
Line with aluminum foil. Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press on bottom.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and chill. Serve with beef.

title: wyatt's eggplant casserole
directions: Cut eggplant into 1-inch cubes and soak in salt water in refrigerator overnight (at least 6 hours).
Drain and place in pan.
Cover with water and simmer until tender.
Soak crumbs in milk.
Saute onions, green peppers and celery in margarine for 15 minutes.
Combine eggplant, pimento and seasonings; blend thoroughly.
Place in greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Beat in sugars, flour, butter, oil and vanilla until well blended. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack. Chill until serving. Refrigerate leftovers. Yield: 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Put the pot on the stove with a little water in it.
Put some dough in the water.
Them put it all in a tiny bowl and put it in the microwave for 10 minutes.
Roll it into balls and put it on a pan in the oven for 20 hours and when it's finished you have donuts.
Put on different colors of sprinkles.

title: calico beans
directions: Saute ground beef, bacon and onions.
To make sauce, combine vinegar, catsup, salt, mustard and brown sugar.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot.

title: german pancakes
directions: In
blender,
mix
eggs, salt, flour and milk.
Preheat oven to
Heat
a
10-inch
skillet
with
3 tablespoons butter until
sizzling, but not brown.
Put batter in skillet. Bake 10 minutes, reduce heat to 375° and bake 20 to 30 minutes more.
Do not brown too much.

title: turkey-mushroom salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Blend together mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion and salt.
Add to turkey mixture; toss lightly. Chill.
Line bowl with romaine leaves.
Spoon in salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave candy turtles
directions: Melt
chips,
margarine
and
marshmallows
in
2 quart casserole in microwave oven for 3 minutes, stirring once.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: old fashioned sweet potatoes
directions: Grate uncooked sweet potatoes into baking dish.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Dot with butter.
Add enough orange juice to be visible (do not cover with orange juice).
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; stir.
Spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Crush cereal; stir in 1/4 cup butter and sprinkle over the potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: diane's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except tomato sauce) in a mixing bowl. Shape into loaf or put in a loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes covered. Remove from oven pour tomato sauce over top and continue to bake 15 minutes more uncovered or until done.

title: pink delight
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and cherries.
Fold in pineapple, marshmallows, Cool Whip and food coloring for color.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar, Cool Whip and buttermilk or sour cream.
Add pineapple, banana and strawberries and pour into a long casserole (such as a bread loaf pan).
Freeze.

title: strawberry compote
directions: Alternate layers of strawberries, sour cream and sprinkling of brown sugar in 6 compotes.
Chill until ready to serve.	Yield: 6 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad or dessert
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze overnight.

title: pasta lite
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package. Drain. Use cauliflower and broccoli, as much as you like. Mix all together with all ingredients. Keep in fridge.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger in a skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and celery until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, stir, simmer 5 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream the oleo, oil and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add alternately with flour and 7-Up to mixture.
Grease pan and bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and water.
Cook until hard ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Add peanuts.
Cook until peanuts turn golden brown.

title: sandollars
directions: Cream first three ingredients.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder, salt and chips.
Stir until blended and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pickled red beets
directions: Cook beets until tender (after cutting off greens and stems), then slide off skin and rest of stem.
Slice beets.
Cook water, vinegar, sugar and cloves about 5 minutes.
Then add sliced beets and simmer about ??? minutes.
Cool.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sift 1 cup of sugar with dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Beat well.
Pour in melted butter.
Top with cherries and sprinkle with remaining sugar. Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Chill milk in ice tray until almost frozen around edges.
In a 2-quart bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water, then stir in cold water.
Add marshmallows, undrained crushed pineapple and broken nuts to gelatin.
Whip milk in cold bowl until stiff.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Cover and chill.

title: fanny may's chocolate fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter, vanilla and milk for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until creamy and put in a jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inch).
Freezes well.
Cut in small pieces.

title: sausage pie
directions: Cook sausage until done. Crumble and drain.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Put in shell.
Beat eggs. Combine remaining ingredients and add to eggs.
Pour in shell. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ritzy pie
directions: Bring water, cream of tartar and sugar to boil.
Add Ritz crackers.
(Do not break, keep whole.
The secret; individual squares, approximately 1 1/2 inches square.)
Cook for 2 minutes; do not stir.
Pour mixture on bottom pie crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Dot with dabs of butter.
Put on top crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: carrots lyonnaise
directions: Pare carrots and cut in strips. Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/3 cup water. Add carrots and cook uncovered 10 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions.
Cook covered 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and add 3/4 cup water. Bring to a boil.
Add carrots and chicken stock.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes or until tender.
Add pinch of sugar.

title: tonya's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a greased casserole dish.

title: green vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl, mix together green beans, peas, corn, celery, green peppers, onions and pimientos.
In saucepan, mix together sugar, oil, vinegar, salt, black pepper and water.
Cook over heat until mixture boils.
Cool completely before pouring over vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: opelousas rice dressing
directions: Brown meat.
Add salt, peppers, onion and bell pepper.
Wilt the onion and bell pepper.
Sprinkle garlic powder and mix well with meat mixture.
Add rice; mix thoroughly.
Add green onions. Serve piping hot.

title: beer bottom chicken
directions: Marinate chicken for 1 - 2 hours.
Insert 1/2 medium onion into chicken cavity and push to top.
Open can of beer and discard half.
You have your way, I have mine! Set chicken onto remaining 1/2 can of beer, forming a tripod with legs and beer can.
Grill over medium heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until you can shake hands with your chicken.
Baste occasionally with leftover marinade.
Let chicken cool, remove beer can and onion.
Cut up and serve.

title: peaches 'n crumb cake
directions: Combine 1/2 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Add 2 tablespoons softened oleo and hot tap water to dry ingredients. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add egg and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup flour.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: three cheese macaroni(make one-quart - freeze one!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
To a pot of slightly salted boiling water, add macaroni.
Cook for 6 minutes.
Drain and return to pot. Set aside.

title: collard greens stem relish
directions: Wash the vegetables and
cut into fine pieces; put into pot and cover with lid.
Cook until tender (about 45 minutes). Sterilize jars and fill jars with vegetables approximately 3/4 full from top.
Seal jars
as
directed
with
canning jar instructions.
Store in refrigerator.
Relish
may	be
used
in potato salad, tuna salad,
