macaroni salad, toss salad, greens, cabbage, hamburgers, wieners, etc.

title: bottled hot sauce
directions: Mix chopped hot peppers with 1/2 cup vinegar.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Add rest of vinegar and all of catsup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes and pour into sterilized jars.
Seal.
This is the answer to hot sauce.

title: osgood pie
directions: Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven until done.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Chop
walnuts
into
medium
size
pieces;
beat
eggs, gradually beat in sugar and oil.
Combine dry ingredients; add to first mixture gradually with zucchini.
Stir in raisins and vanilla.
Turn into a
lightly
greased
and floured loaf pan. Bake
at 350° for 55 minutes until loaf tests done.
Let stand 10 minutes; turn out onto wire rack to cool.
Makes 2 loaves. Freezes well.

title: flounder florentine
directions: Melt the butter.
Sprinkle in dill, garlic, dry mustard, parsley and other seasonings.
Stir.
Thicken with flour paste. Sauce it with white wine or milk.
Wash flounder fillets in cold water; pat dry.
Butter an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Lay 2 of the fillets on bottom.
Put the spinach on top and pour half of the sauce on spinach.
Lay the other 2 fillets on top and add rest of sauce.
Bake at 350° until fish is done and sauce is bubbly, about 25 minutes.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat in 4 portions.
Combine flour and salt and pound into meat.
Save remaining flour.
Brown in hot Crisco (oil).
Transfer to shallow baking dish.
Blend flour into drippings; add carrots, celery, onion, tomatoes and Worcestershire.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, until tender.
Add broth or water if necessary while cooking.
Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Bake until melted. Makes 4 servings.

title: pinto delight
directions: Soak pinto beans in hot water for 1 hour.
Add ground beef, salt and black pepper.
Cook slowly for 3 hours.

title: barbecued country spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut spareribs into strips.
Lay in roasting pan fat side up.
Arrange onion slices over spareribs. Bake for 25 minutes until they begin to brown.
Combine all other ingredients into small pan; mix well.
Bring to boil.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Pour sauce over spareribs.
Turn, coating with sauce. Bake 1 hour or until tender, basting every 15 minutes with sauce. Yield:
4 servings.

title: daddy's rich fudge
directions: Butter an 8-inch or 9-inch dish.
In a heavy, large saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a rolling boil. Then, boil without stirring, until soft ball stage (forms a soft ball when dropped into very cold water).
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
(If adding peanut butter, do so now.)
Cool for about 10 minutes.
Beat by hand until it thickens and begins to lose some of the gloss.
Spread into a buttered dish.

title: welsh pork pasties
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Blend all filling ingredients.
For crust, soften butter or margarine in warm water and blend with biscuit mix.
Knead dough 3 or 4 times on lightly floured surface.
Divide dough into fourths.
Roll each fourth into 8-inch circle.
Divide pork mixture into fourths and place on bottom half of each circle. Dampen edges of dough with water.
Fold in half; roll and tuck edges to seal.
Make a 1/2-inch slit on top of each pastie.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie crust until brown.
Peel tomatoes and quarter.
Mix mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese and add to tomatoes.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour fish kabobs
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in cold juice.
Add tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, chopped onion and ginger.
Simmer on stove top in microwave until sauce is thickened (about 4 minutes).

title: lentil, potato and ham soup(makes 6 servings)
directions: In medium pot, put 6 cups water, lentils, onion and potatoes. Bring to boil.
Cut back to simmer and cook covered 25 to 30 minutes.
Add onion and ham and simmer 5 minutes more.
Add lemon and salt and pepper.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Cut oleo into sugar; add eggs, bananas and milk.
Add dry ingredients. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be used for cupcakes.
Makes 1 large loaf or 3 mini loaves.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Grease 16 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Start oven 10 minutes before baking; set at 350°.
Sift flour, measure, re-sift 3 times with cocoa and sugar.
In a large mixing bowl, add butter, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Stir in nuts.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until barely done.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add milk and butter.
Pour ingredients into pan and put fruit on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla together until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350°
for 1/2 hour.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling.

title: frankfurter supper dish
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Drop franks into boiling water and heat 6 minutes.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.
Make Cream Sauce, stirring in Worcestershire sauce.
Stir beans and franks into Cream Sauce. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add broth to make a moist mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Freezes well uncooked.

title: heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions, using two 9-inch round cake pans and let cool. Frost the bottom layer of the cake round and sprinkle with 1/2 of the chopped 3 Musketeers brand miniatures. Place second layer of cake on the top and frost. Decorate with remaining 3 Musketeers brand miniatures.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter.
Cook broccoli acccording to directions on package and drain well.
Mix celery, onions and broccoli with cooked rice, Cheez Whiz and soup.
Place in baking dish.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot meringue pie
directions: Sift together cornstarch and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks and blend thoroughly.
Add scalded milk slowly.
Cook in top of double boiler, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add salt and vanilla.
Fold in 1/2 cup apricots which have been mashed through a sieve.
Cool and pour into cooked shell.
Top with the following meringue.

title: cajun chili
directions: Combine beef, sausage, onion, peppers and garlic in a large cooker and brown.
Drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients and cook on medium for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with lots of cool drink.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread in small pieces; soak in 2 cups water and 1 cup milk.
Mix all ingredients, except raisins.
Roll raisins in 2 tablespoons of flour; spoon in mixture.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Blend vinegar slowly into mustard in saucepan.
Add water, sugar, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and whole cloves.
Simmer for 10 minutes: cool.
Pour over eggs and onions.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
Marinade may be used for a second dozen eggs: it is also a good salad dressing.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, one cup chopped nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into three well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: chicken-bacon and cheddar sandwiches
directions: Place each chicken breast between 2 pieces of wax paper. Pound chicken until about 1/4-inch thick; set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove and drain.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of drippings to cook chicken in for 6 to 8 minutes.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard; blend well.
Spread mayonnaise mixture on cut sides of rolls.
Take bottom half of each roll and put on chicken breast, 1 slice cooked bacon, 1 tomato slice and 1 lettuce leaf.
Cover each with top half.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda together and mix with butter mixture.
Add mashed bananas and vanilla, mix well.
Add buttermilk and nuts and stir well. Pour in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch lightly greased loaf pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: butter pecan turtle bars
directions: Cut 1/2 cup softened butter into 1 cup brown sugar and all-purpose flour.
When well mixed, pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle pecans evenly over unbaked crust and press lightly.

title: pie crust for fried pies
directions: Cut together with fork 1 cup flour, powdered milk, salt and Crisco.
Add cold water and mix together as for any pie crust. Add 1 more cup flour.
Will make 16 pies the size of a saucer.

title: garden barley soup
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan or Dutch oven, combine tomato juice, broth and barley. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until barley and vegetables are tender, stirring once in awhile to keep from sticking.
Makes approximately 9 (1 cup) servings.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Drop with teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil the sweet potatoes or yams until center of potatoes are soft.
Mash the potatoes, then add butter, eggs, sugar, milk, extracts and cinnamon.

Blend until batter is smooth (no lumps). Set aside for 30 minutes and pour into an 8-inch pie plate or pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes until browned on top. When pie is done, center of pie should be solid.
Serve warm or cold.

title: potato crepes
directions: Soften cream cheese in mixing bowl.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Add eggs, salt and pepper.
Beat with electric mixer. Stir in cheese, potatoes, cream, chives and mushrooms.
Lightly oil electric skillet and heat to temperature just below that recommended for pancakes.
When heated, add small amount of butter and ladle potato batter into skillet to make crepes 3 inches in diameter.

title: grilled potatoes(easy and great for summer picnics)
directions: Wash and pat dry potatoes.
Slice potatoes crosswise until 1/4-inch from bottom.
Put generous amount of butter between slices.
Sprinkle between slices with garlic salt, parsley and cheese. Wrap tightly in tinfoil.
Place on grill for 45 minutes.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Grease skillet and sprinkle thin layer of meat in bottom.
Pour half of batter in skillet.
Sprinkle meat, onion, jalapeno peppers and cheese (one at a time) over batter.
Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy banana nut bread
directions: Combine eggs, water, vanilla, margarine and bananas. Mix thoroughly. Stir in cake mix. Beat well. Stir in nuts. Pour into a 10-inch greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden.

title: zucchini and tomato bake
directions: Place zucchini in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 each:
soy sauce, salt, garlic salt, and pepper.
Layer tomatoes and onion over zucchini.
Sprinkle with remaining seasoning.
Top with cheese and dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: persimmon drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Beat thoroughly persimmon pulp, baking soda, sugar, shortening and margarine.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on prepared pans.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: salad crab louie
directions: Place crab, lettuce, onion, celery and tomato in a bowl.
Toss with mayonnaise.
Place on lettuce leaf.
Garnish with sliced egg and strips of pimento.
Serve with Melba toast or hot buttered English muffins.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and cocoa in top of double boiler.
Gradually stir in sugar.
Add milk slowly to blend well.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Serve over ice cream or cake.

title: pull taffy
directions: Put into deep saucepan.
Cook over low heat.
Stir well until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to a hard boil stage (280°).
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and pour into a shallow buttered pan to cool.
When edges of candy stiffen, fold them to the center with a spatula.
Coat hand with butter.
When cool enough to handle, pull candy until light cream color, stretch and twist into rope or braid 3 strands.
Cut into 1 inch pieces.

title: key largo - key lime pie
directions: Combine milk and egg yolks at low speed.
Slowly add juice, mixing until well blended and thickened.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Refrigerate until cool. Top with whipped cream or meringue.

title: 10 layer salad
directions: Place lettuce in large bowl.
Add rest of ingredients in order, in layers over lettuce.
Top with mayonnaise that has been mixed with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle grated cheese over mayonnaise.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
This looks good fixed in large glass bowl so layers show.

title: pork chop barbecue
directions: Mix water, vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt and peppers.
Add lemon and onion.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add the ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and liquid smoke.
Bring to a boil.
Place pork chops in a dish and pour sauce over them.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven 1 hour and 25 minutes, turning chops over once or until chops are done.
I usually make a double batch of sauce, because I find that one is not enough.

title: white satin frosting
directions: Put sugar, water and corn syrup in saucepan; stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Boil, covered, about 3 minutes, then boil, uncovered and without stirring, until soft ball forms when dropped in cold water.
Remove syrup from heat, quickly. Beat whites with cream of tartar until stiff, but not dry, then pour syrup over egg whites, beating.
Add salt and flavoring; beat until frosting is cool.
Spread.

title: vince early's greens
directions: Fry bacon, retaining grease. Add cleaned, chopped collards to water in a large pot. Add bacon grease, salt and pepper, bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for about 2 hours or until greens are tender. Add ham steak and okra and cook an additional 30 minutes. Crumble bacon on top to serve.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and gradually mix in pineapple.
Add 1 cup pecans, pepper, onions and salt.
Chill well, about 1 hour, then form into a ball.
Roll in remaining pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Separate 12 Oreos; scrape off the cream and save it.
Crush finely the 12 Oreos.
Mix milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Crush remaining Oreos and fold them along with the saved cream into the mixture.
Pour into a deep dish.
Sprinkle the saved Oreos on top so that no white shows and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add beaten egg, onion, cheese, mayonnaise and soup.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix margarine and stuffing mix and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bonnie's pralines
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in heavy pan and stir on medium heat for 20 to 30 minutes to soft-ball stage.
Turn off heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until creamy and sticky.
Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Combine all ingredients.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes, then cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes more until done.

title: oatmeal-caramel bars
directions: Combine caramels and milk in a saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until caramels melt.
Set mixture aside.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix and cream sugar and oleo.
Add flour, cocoa and eggs. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 300°.
Take out of oven. Spread marshmallows evenly on cake.
Put back in oven until they melt.
Cool before icing.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let thicken.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Can also sprinkle nuts on top, if you wish.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon slices in large pan.
Drain and crumble, save grease in small bowl.
Mix vinegar, water, sugar and flour.
Pour into bacon grease, stir until thick over medium heat.
Stir potatoes, onion and bacon in.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs and add one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: tex mex dip
directions: First Layer:
Spread refried beans and jalapeno in bottom of dish.

title: hot slaw
directions: Cook shredded cabbage with a little water, 15 to 20 minutes. Mix the egg, sugar, salt and vinegar together well.
Pour over hot cabbage, cook an additional 5 minutes.

title: taffy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and cream of tartar in saucepan. Cook until sugar melts.
Cook without stirring to very hard ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into greased platter.
When cool enough to handle, pull until white, twist and cut.

title: layered deli sandwich
directions: Cut bread horizontally to form 3 layers and a top.
Put ham, Swiss cheese, and mustard on bottom layer.	Put roast beef, horseradish sauce, and cheddar cheese on next layer.
Put turkey, mayonnaise, and provolone cheese on top layer.
Top with bread crown.
Wrap well and place in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in wedges and serve.
Serves 9-14.
Great for party.

title: mother's lemon pie
directions: In saucepan or double boiler, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Pour boiling water over.
When about boiling, add lemon and eggs mixed together.
Cook.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook meatballs in shortening in 12-inch skillet until brown.
Remove meatballs from skillet; drain fat.

title: texas okra patties
directions: Combine okra, onion, salt, pepper, water and egg.
Mix baking powder and cornmeal; stir into the first mixture.
Drop by tablespoonful into hot oil and brown over medium heat.
Drain on paper towels.
Make 8 or more patties.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Melt butter.
Pour 2 tablespoons into 2 (10-inch) cake pans. Divide nuts and sprinkle in each pan.
Mix water and brown sugar into remaining butter.
Bring to boil and cook 1 minute or make a syrup.
Dip biscuits in syrup and place 10 in each pan.
Pour remaining syrup around biscuits.
Bake as directed on biscuit package or until done in center.
Serve on plate.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate the crescent rolls into four rectangles and seal perforations.
Blend the cream cheese and melted oleo until smooth.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon 1/2 cup of the mixture into center of each rectangle. Roll the four corners of the dough to center and seal.
Brush tops with melted oleo and sprinkle with seasoned croutons.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes until golden.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake golf ball sized cookies.
Place 2 inches apart and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
The recipe makes 112 cookies.

title: grandma kline's baked beans
directions: Fry 1/2 pound bacon with onion and celery to taste.
Mix beans, fried bacon with onion and celery, tomato puree, catsup, molasses, salt and brown sugar in roasting pan.
Place 1/2 pound of bacon on top.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a pan on medium heat.
When it starts to boil, cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and oats.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Combine water, bouillon, minced onion and
minced garlic; let stand for 10 minutes.
Add oil, vinegar, tarragon and black pepper.
Place potatoes in shallow 3 quart casserole.
Pour dressing over all, tossing to coat.

title: yogurt
directions: Heat milk to 190°.
Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water; add to milk when it reaches 190°.
Cool to 130°.
Add vanilla, yogurt and sugar.
Beat until smooth; cover and put in oven with just the pilot overnight or like 5 hours, until set.
Take out and beat well again, then cool.
Pie filling, red raspberry and grape are very delicious added.

title: dill beans
directions: Leave beans whole; cook until barely tender.
Pack in jars with a head of dill (stalks or leaves will do), a piece of garlic the size of a pea or less and pinch of alum for crispness.
Boil vinegar, water and salt solution and pour over beans in jar. Process in hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: stewed tomatoes and okra(diabetic)
directions: Cook okra according to package directions; drain.
Cook onion and bell pepper in oil until tender.
Add seasoning, okra and tomatoes.
Cook on low heat until bubbly.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together with hands until well mixed.
Bake in large loaf pan in slow oven at 350° for about 1 hour.
Use sauce, whipped cream or light icing if you like.

title: crunchy romaine salad
directions: Crunch noodles. Brown
noodles and walnuts in butter and drain. Chop broccoli, onions and lettuce. Add nuts and noodles into lettuce mixture.

title: tomato primavera soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add mushrooms, onion, pepper, carrots and celery; cook until onion is almost tender.
Add zucchini; cook 1 minute.
Stir in water, tomatoes and beef broth; heat to boiling.
Stir in uncooked pasta; heat to boiling.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 8 to 10 minutes, or until pasta is tender. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain noodles in a large pan. Saute onion and green pepper in margarine for 3 minutes.
Add beef; cook until no longer pink.
Drain off fat.
In a bowl, combine tomato paste and sour cream; stir in the noodles and cottage cheese.
Layer half the noodle mixture, top with half beef mixture. Repeat layers.
Pour tomato sauce evenly over the top of casserole. Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until bubbly hot.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk into a batter and pour over butter.
Spoon fruit over the batter and butter.
Pour juice over all this and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375° until batter has cooked thoroughly and has browned.
This works with any fruit.

title: mexican cheddar chicken
directions: Cook chicken in skillet in hot oil 4 to 5 minutes or until browned.
Stir in rice, tomatoes and salsa.
Reduce heat to low; cover.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Sprinkle with cheese.
Continue cooking about 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: deluxe peach ice cream
directions: Combine peaches and 1 cup sugar; stir well and set aside. Beat eggs until frothy.
Combine next 3 ingredients; stir well. Gradually add to eggs; beat until thick.

Add milk; mix well. Pour into a large saucepan; cook on low, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and coats a metal spoon about 15 minutes. Remove from heat and set pan in cold water; stir gently until cool.
Stir in whipping cream and vanilla.
Add peaches, stirring well.
Pour mixture into 1 gallon freezer container; freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
Let ripen at least 1 hour before serving.

title: granny smith apple pies
directions: Peel and slice 2 apples very thin.
Roll 1 can biscuits out very thin.
Place apples over 1/2 of rolled biscuit.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Fold dough over and press down.
Place each pie in a baking dish in a single layer.

title: fruit cocktail bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla. Add the fruit cocktail.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Spread in greased 15 x 10-inch pan. Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crab stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Drain and cool.
In large bowl, stir together crabmeat, cheese, parsley and horseradish. Stuff each shell with about 1 tablespoon mixture.
Pour 1 cup sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place shells in pan and cover with remaining sauce.
Cover with foil.
(Can be prepared to this point and baked later.)
Bake 35 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple and cottage cheese.
Mix in dry jello. Mix in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: bean casserole
directions: Do not add salt or pepper.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes in 5-quart Dutch oven.

title: sweet squash pickles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and set aside for 2 hours after putting ice on top of mixture. Mix vinegar, celery seed, sugar and turmeric in large stockpot. Drain the mixture of peppers, squash, onions and salt. Add the mixture to the pot. Bring to a boil. Add to clean, dry, warm jars and seal.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Place egg yolks, sugar, cornstarch, cocoa and milk into blender.
Blend on high until mixed well.
Pour into microwave-safe mixing bowl.
Microwave for 2 minute increments.
Stir well with a whisk after each timing.
It will take 4 to 5 two-minute timings to get thick.
Don't over-thicken because as the pie cools, it will become firm.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour mixture into a cooked pie shell.
As I am cooking the pie mixture, I cook the pie shell according to package directions.
Top with meringue and bake until lightly brown in 400° oven.

title: caramel cereal pops(16 pops)
directions: Unwrap caramels and put in a saucepan.	Add milk.
Melt on medium,
until
caramels
are
creamy,
about
15 minutes. Remove from heat.	Stir in cereal and peanuts.
Stir until all cereal and
peanuts
are
evenly coated with caramel mixture. Grease with
shortening
an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spoon cereal into pan and press down evenly.
Let mixture stand for 1
hour or until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares, then insert a wooden stick on one end of each square.	Enjoy!!

title: turtle cake
directions: Make cake mix according to directions.
Pour half of batter into greased pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels and butter with Milnot and pour over cake.
Sprinkle nuts, then chocolate chips over cake.
Top with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with more chopped nuts, if desired, and bake for 20 minutes.

title: tender flaky pie crust
directions: Mix flour, lard and salt together until they resemble coarse corn meal.
Add vinegar and water.
Mix just to hold ingredients together.
Makes 3 single crusts.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook beef until fat coats pan.
Add onions and cook until beef is brown.
Stir in tomatoes and seasonings and bring to a boil. Combine cooked macaroni and turn into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.
Freezes well.

title: beef-zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion
and
beef
together in skillet.
Season to taste. Arrange cooked zucchini, sliced, with meat mixture and grated cheese in alternate layers in casserole.
Pour mushroom soup over top
and
top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. It usually tastes better reheated.

title: spinach chicken
directions: Combine cheeses and garlic powder in small bowl.
Add defrosted spinach.
Slice breasts in half.
Fill with mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush wafers, then add sugar, butter and juice.
Blend well. Finally roll into balls and cover with coconut or crushed pecans.

title: aline's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, syrup, nuts, salt, vanilla and chipped up butter.
Put into unbaked 9-inch deep dish pie shell and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple date nut loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and lemon extract.
Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts to creamed mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dates and mix well, separating date pieces.
Stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture, alternating with reserved pineapple juice plus 1/4 cup water.
Fold in cherries.
Bake at 375° about 55 minutes.

title: sugar-free finger jello
directions: In large bowl, combine Knox gelatine and Jell-O.
Add boiling water until dissolved.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: oven meal
directions: Put into pan (cake pan) in order given.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° for
1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine.
Cut in butter until mixture clings together.
Press in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine eggs, sugar (granulated) and lemon juice.
Sift flour and baking powder; stir into egg mixture.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Cool and sprinkle 4x sugar over it.
Cut in bars.
Yield: 30.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Put dried beef in blender or food processor and shred it (reserve 1/4 cup).
Mix shredded beef with the cream cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Roll into a ball and coat with remaining 1/4 cup beef.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: brownies with frosting
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir until just mixed.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Cover and chill.
Shape into ball and roll in crushed walnuts.
Serve with your choice of crackers.

title: dessert nut butter horns
directions: Add flour, salt and yeast, cut in butter, add egg yolks, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well, do not use mixer, form into 5 to 6 balls and set aside.

title: italian meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, half of tomato sauce, egg, 1/2 teaspoon oregano, salt and pepper.
On wax paper, pat into a rectangle 1/2 to 1-inch thick.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella; roll up by starting on short side; lift paper until meat begins to roll tightly.
Peel back paper to keep it free.
Roll up completely; seal edges and place in glass loaf dish.
Microwave at High for 9 minutes, rotating dish after half the cooking time.
Drain; combine remaining tomato sauce and oregano; pour over meat loaf.
Sprinkle with Parmesan; microwave 2 minutes to heat sauce.
Tent with foil and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cheesecake
directions: Butter a spring-form pan (10-inch pan), bottom and sides. Sprinkle sides with 2 tablespoons of crushed crumbs without butter.
Mix rest of crumbs with butter and sugar; pack firmly on bottom of pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and chopped onion in salted water until tender, about 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Add celery soup, 1/2 stick butter, Velveeta cheese (cut up in little chunks), milk, salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Stir well.
Put in buttered casserole dish and top with crushed crackers that have been sauteed in 1/2 stick butter.
Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: kings coffee
directions: Combine coffee and water.
Add cinnamon.
Chill.
Pour cinnamon-flavored coffee into 6 chilled glasses filled with crushed ice.
Top with whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: honduran cole slaw
directions: Mix together and chill. This is tangy so you might need the sugar!

title: stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a stew pot.
Add additional water, if needed.
Cook until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: dump cake
directions: Place dry cake mix over top of pineapple and apple or cherry pie mix in 9 X 13 cake pan.
Mix with pineapple and juice.
Add 1 box white or yellow cake mix.
2 cubes of butter or oleo.
Cut into butter pats and spread generously over cake mix. (Butter or margarine can be melted and drizzled over cake mix.)
Sprinkle nuts (almonds, walnuts, pecans, your choice).
Cover the top of mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool.
Serve with whipping cream or ice cream.
Easy and delicious.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; reserve broth.
Saute celery and onion.
Stir in soups.
Cook noodles in broth according to package directions. Drain and mix all together in a casserole dish.
Grate cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix dry jello with Cool Whip.
Add cottage cheese.
Add drained fruit; refrigerate.

title: green bean & shiitake mushroom  sauté
directions: Cook beans until good and tender.
In a large non stick skillet over medium-high heat cook mushrooms and onion in hot oil for 5 minutes, stirring.
Add garlic and thyme to mushrooms; cook, stirring, 1 minute more.
Stir in broth, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper; bring to a boil, scraping the bottom of the pan with a wooden spoon.
When ready to serve, pour over green beans, and toss to coat. Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar and press into bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Mix ingredients except hamburger and simmer for 20 minutes. Add hamburger and cook until done.
May be used on buns or on hot dogs as you would chili.

title: quick-baked pasta
directions: Bring 4 cups water to a boil.
Add oil to frying pan and add hamburger and garlic.
Saute until tender, then drain excess fat. Add all remaining ingredients except the Mozzarella cheese and the pasta.
Simmer the mixture while the pasta cooks until just barely tender.
Drain pasta and mix with the sauce.
Pour all into a 3-quart baking dish and top with the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tuna puffs
directions: Mix tuna, Miracle Whip, chopped celery and chopped green onion.
Refrigerate.
Make cream puffs.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and bacon.
Add chopped onion.
In large baking bowl add rest of ingredients.
Stir meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be frozen before or after baking.
I always double this.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate molasses lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop by spoons onto foil-lined cookie sheets, 3 inches apart and spread out thin.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool completely (15 minutes); peel off foil.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on flat side of half the cookies and stick
together with remaining half of cookies.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Peel, cook and mash several potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste, butter and milk.
In a skillet, cook hamburger, onion, bouillon cubes and Worcestershire sauce for 20 minutes, covered. Add water if needed.
Add peas and carrots; cook until tender. With a slotted spoon, put meat mixture into a casserole dish.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Top with grated cheese and place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: fish and chip bake
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package directions, except reduce water by 1/4 cup.
Stir in drained spinach, sour cream and pepper. Turn into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Dip one side of each fillet in milk, then in stuffing mix.
Fold fillets in half, coating side out.
Place atop potato mixture; drizzle with melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until fish flakes easily when tested with fork, 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with lemon slices. Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add broth, chicken, salt and cumin; heat until hot.
Make sauce of cream of chicken soup, sour cream, chilies and small amount of picante sauce.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushroom pieces in butter.
Add drained cooked broccoli, golden mushroom soup and bacon cheese.
Heat and serve as a warm dip with tortilla chips.
May be made ahead of time and frozen.

title: swiss ham and potato soup
directions: In medium saucepan over low heat, heat all ingredients, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 4 cups or 3 servings.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 2 cups flour and baking powder with melted oleo.
Reserve 1/2 mixture.
Pat the rest in bottom of pan.
Drain cans of cherries, putting juice in pot with 2 cups sugar and 3 tablespoons flour, mixed.
Put cherries on top of crunch.
Cook juice until slightly thickened. Pour over top of cherries.
Add additional crunch and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dawn's soup
directions: Skin potatoes and boil alone.
Cook beef in pan alone.	Put tomato juice, salt, pepper and garlic salt in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Then turn to medium and add chopped onions.
Add peas, potatoes and beef when done and last, add corn.
Let simmer for about 1 hour on low heat.
Will be good and done when onions are clear.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions and cool.
Crumble 1/2 of cake in large bowl.
Spread 1/2 of strawberries, pudding, glaze and Cool Whip.
Crumble rest of cake, spread strawberries, glaze and pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Place vegetables in sprayed pie pan.
Beat remaining ingredients together.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients and make into balls (small or large) and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and pour off any excess fat from dish.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Blend in flour and eggs.
Gradually add milk, then flavoring and coconut.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° in 2 greased and floured pie pans.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil ingredients for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool in cold water.
Beat until thick.

title: peppermint candy ice cream
directions: Add crushed peppermint candy to any vanilla ice cream recipe after it has frozen for about 15 minutes.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening. Add egg and milk all at once.
Mix until dough forms a ball.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface and knead 10 to 12 times. Roll out and cut.
(Do not roll very thin.)
Bake on lightly greased baking sheet at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: caramel coffee cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift into bowl with sugars and salt. Cut in shortening with pastry blender until it is crumbly. Measure out 1 cup of this mixture and set aside for topping. Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to beaten egg.
Stir in remaining crumb mixture.
Pour into a wax paper-lined 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle the 1 cup of crumb mixture over batter. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cindy's chile rellenos
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain grease.
Set aside. Spread chiles on bottom of dish, approximately 10 x 10-inch. Cover with ground beef and onion mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over chile and hamburger mixture.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut pockets in chops.
Combine onion and celery in skillet and saute.
Add rest of stuffing and mix well.
Stuff pockets.
Place chops in foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sinful chocolate cake
directions: Prepare oblong cake pan with shortening and flour.
Layer coconut and coarsely chopped pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix and pour over coconut and pecans.
Melt butter and cream cheese in microwave.
Mix in powdered sugar with spoon. Pour over top of cake leaving about 1/2 inch away from top of pan. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pink cloud
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Allow to cool.
Stir in strawberries and thawed whipped topping.
Break cake into small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour strawberry mixture over cake.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.
Cut into squares and serve.
(Any flavor gelatin and any fruit can be substituted.)

title: blueberry pudding
directions: In a food processor, blend the cottage cheese until smooth, about 3 minutes.
Add the blueberries and blend again until smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl. Whisk in the yogurt, lemon juice and honey.
Divide the mixture among 6 custard cups.
Chill before serving.
Serves 6.

title: red italian dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in blender.
Ready to serve.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Coat chicken pieces and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lindsey's chicken chowder
directions: In saucepan combine chicken, water, onion, carrots, garlic, bouillon granules and pepper, bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in potatoes; simmer, covered, about 15 minutes more or until chicken and potatoes are tender.
Remove chicken.
When cool, cut into bite size pieces.
Return to pan. Mash potatoes slightly.
Combine milk and cornstarch; add to saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 more minutes.
May sprinkle with chives.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook hamburger, vinegar, water, salt and onion until done. Fold in ketchup, brown sugar, celery and dry mustard.

title: b.b.q. salmon
directions: Spread a thin layer of mayonnaise on meat of fish.

title: date cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add alternately the milk and mixture of dry ingredients.
Beat thoroughly.
Add dates.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, margarine, oil, vanilla, sour milk and shredded zucchini.
Blend dry ingredients with egg mixture; add chocolate chips and walnuts.
Bake in greased and floured bread pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: diabetic banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix, 2% milk, vanilla and Cool Whip.
Then put a layer of cookies and bananas in dish until all gone.
Pour pudding over top of cookies and bananas.

title: filled ham schnitzel
directions: Brown mushrooms in butter with parsley.
Add 1 tablespoon flour; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Cool.
Spread mixture on 1/2 of each slice of ham.
Fold other half over; press to secure.
Dip schnitzel in eggs, then in 1/2 cup flour.
Put back into egg and then into crumbs.
Brown on both sides in hot shortening.

title: chocolate bourbon pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine eggs, sugars, corn syrup, butter, bourbon, flour, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Stir well. Sprinkle chocolate chips over pie shell.
Pour filling over chips and arrange pecan halves on top.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes longer or until set. Serve with whipped cream.

title: hot cranberry tea(serves 12)
directions: Bring to boil.
Keep warm in percolator.
Great for winter and Christmas.
Use 2 large cinnamon sticks for group serving.

title: irish scone
directions: Mix the first five ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs, milk and melted butter.
Add caraway seed as desired.
Stir by hand.
Butter and lightly flour 3 large loaf pans.
Put mixture into 3 buttered loaf pans.
Bake at 380° for one hour.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese; gradually add powdered sugar. Beat until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.

title: sue's cheese pecan wafers
directions: Cream the cheese with butter.
Mash all other ingredients together with cheese mixture.
Add pecans, then add red pepper to taste.
Roll into "log" and place in freezer.
When ready to use, cut thin slices and bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Roll breasts in oil and margarine mixture, then in mixture of Parmesan, cracker crumbs and garlic salt.
Pour 1/2 cup hot water into a 9 x 9-inch glass casserole.
Place chicken breasts on top and cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 6.
Great with sour cream noodles!

title: taco salad
directions: Spread refried beans on a dish.
Mix taco seasoning and sour cream.
Spread over beans.
Put the onion and tomato on top of those ingredients and then put cheese on top of that.
Dip with taco chips.

title: sun-drop pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs one
at a time, beating well after each.
Add extracts and flour. Mix
until	blended
well.	Add Sun-Drop last.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crumb cake(esther's)
directions: Mix sugar, shortening (Spry), cinnamon, flour and nuts. Take out 1/2 cup for topping. Mix the remaining ingredients with the rest of mix. Put in greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 10.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, biscuit mix, eggs and vanilla at medium speed until well combined.
Add nuts, coconut and chocolate chips last; blend in by hand.
Mixture will be very thick.

title: date nut roll
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Cook over medium heat about 10 minutes or until thick.
Add Rice Krispies and chopped nuts.
Roll into balls and then coconut.

title: mom's sweet roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all other ingredients, except only half of flour.
Gradually add remaining flour.
Mix with hands.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Round in greased bowl, greased side up.
Cover with damp cloth.
Let rise in warm place until double (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down and let rise until double again (30 minutes).

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk.
Mix together all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
I bake these in small loaf pans for same amount of time.
They freeze well and make great holiday gifts.

title: snow balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add vanilla, crumbs, flour, cinnamon and nuts. Mix will and shape into 3/4 inch balls. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Saute bacon in large saucepan until brown.
Add onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Cook until onion is tender.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, salt, oregano and pepper.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Saute chicken in oil in large skillet until all sides brown.
Add chicken to sauce; cover and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain. Pour chicken and sauce over spaghetti in large serving dish. Makes 6 servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Keep enough coconut out to sprinkle on top of pie.
Put everything in blender on liquify.
Butter pie plate.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add oil and milk.
Combine all other ingredients until mixed.
You can use right away or store in a covered dish in refrigerator for up to 4 days.
Roll out to desired thickness, cut and bake at 400° until brown.

title: hot beef dish
directions: Open can of Ro-Tel and put in blender to liquify.
(For those that don't like the chunks.)
Brown meat and onion in frying pan. Add other ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish and put in oven long enough to warm.
When ready to serve, cover with crushed Frito or Dorito chips and top with shredded cheese.
Put back in oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: aunt nancy's rolls
directions: Place butter and sugar in milk.
Heat until butter is melted. Let cool until just warm.
Add yeast/water and eggs.
Add flour gradually and mix, 4 to 5 cups.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Knead until not sticky.
(Keep amount of flour down.) Roll until 3/4-inch thick.
Cut into small rounds.
Pull to flatten.
Slap one side in melted butter.
Fold butter side in, Parker House style.
Put on cookie sheet and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Simmer vegetables in water until tender (10 to 15 minutes). Add remaining
ingredients except parsley. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick and easy breakfast swirls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 9 pan.
In small saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter, orange peel and juice; mix well.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except nuts, in a large bowl. Wet your hands and shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in the chopped peanuts and the candy is ready.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Blend half of the cake mix with the brown sugar, margarine, eggs and water.
Blend in remainder of the cake mix.
Add chocolate chips.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix sugar, sour cream and egg together.
Beat in chocolate mixture, then add flour mixture. Beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured pan 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except Fritos and chill for 30 minutes.
Add Fritos just before serving.
Mix well.

title: spinach and garlic pasta
directions: Wash, drain and chop the spinach.
Cook spinach in chicken stock until the stock is reduced by 2/3 of its original volume. Saute the garlic in olive oil.
Do not let garlic turn brown.
Add spinach and remaining stock to garlic and oil.
Cook until rest of stock is reduced.
Add cooked spaghetti to the mixture.
Simmer and mix lightly for several minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve hot.

title: the blue dragon
directions: In a blender, blend all ingredients for 1 minute on medium speed or longer for a smoother smoothie.
Makes 5 cups.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Melt the half and half, butter, Cheddar cheese and Velveeta cheese together.
Thaw potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes.
Let sit 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed shells neapolitan
directions: Combine soup, lemon juice, oregano, broccoli, tomatoes and tuna.
Stuff about 1/4 cup mixture into each shell.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and cool. Add all other ingredients and chill.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix 2 c. sugar, Karo syrup, and 1/2 c. water.
Bring to boil, and boil for 1 minute.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix together 1/4 c. boiling water, 1/2 c. instant coffee, add to mixture above and cool to room temperature.
Mix vanilla and vodka.
Add to mixture above.
Pour mixture into the 2 empty fifth bottles.
Take the mixture and pour about 1 part to 3 or 4 parts milk.
Depends how strong you like them.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Break pretzels; spread evenly in 9 x 13 dish. Mix 3 tablespoons sugar with melted margarine. Pour over pretzels. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. (Pretzels should taste crunchy.)

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in well-greased hot iron skillet. Bake 20 minutes at 450°.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Place the oil and butter in a shallow baking pan and put into a 375°f. 190°c. gas mark 5 oven to melt.
Set aside.
In a large paper sack, mix the flour and seasonings.
Roll the chicken pieces first in the oil and butter, then shake in the paper sack until coated.
Then place the chicken in the pan, skin side down, and bake for 45 minutes.
Turn over and bake for a further 5-10 minutes, or until the crust begins to bubble.
Serve hot or cold, but the crust is better if the chicken isn't refrigerated before eating.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes whole and peel after cooking.
Slice potatoes into bowl and add diced dill pickles and diced small onion.

title: applesauce nutbread
directions: Mix sugar, applesauce, oil, egg whites and skim milk thoroughly in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in oiled and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: champagne lounge goat cheese spread
directions: Blend the cream cheese and goat cheese.
Add all the herbs and the chopped garlic and shallots, then salt.
Enjoy.

title: chocolate cake #2
directions: You take mushrooms.
You throw up the stuff three times.
Then you put it in the oven and cook it for awhile.
When you take it out, you put the cheese on it.
Cut the cheese into small pieces like a long line or finger.
Then you put the mushrooms on.
Then you put it in the oven and cook it.

title: cheddar-spinach quiche(kish)
directions: Drain spinach well on paper towel.
Toss cheese with flour. Add spinach, milk, eggs, bacon and seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Garnish with additional bacon (add a little bacon grease to mixture).

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
Cream margarine and peanut butter; add sugars and mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour mixture to peanut butter mixture, mixing well. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet; flatten with fork. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except croutons and butter) in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Coat croutons with butter and put on top of casserole for last 15 minutes of baking.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 375°.
Pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ham salad
directions: Place bologna, onion, eggs and cheese through grinder.
Add remaining ingredients to desired level of moistness and taste.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put liquids. Add all dry ingredients and stir with a fork. Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potassium
directions: Slice banana thickly.
Place in microwave-safe bowl. Cover banana with butter and sugar.
Microwave on High for 50 seconds (or until butter melts).

title: bacon wrapped beans
directions: Wrap 6 to 8 green beans in a strip of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Place each bundle in a rectangular pan.
Mix sugar, oleo, garlic powder and soy.
Pour over beans and bacon.
Place covered in refrigerator at least 12 hours.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet waffles
directions: Mix until smooth.
Do not use mixer.
Pour into a greased waffle iron.

title: pie crust(makes 4 crusts)
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Mix vinegar and water.
Add together with egg.
Mix well.
Separate into four equal parts. May be frozen or keeps well in refrigerator.
Form into balls to store.
Roll out crust on floured pastry sheet.

title: quick and easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with peaches and dot with margarine.
Bake at 400° until dough has come to top and browns, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Flour and grease Bundt pan. Sprinkle powdered sugar, coconut and nuts in the bottom of the pan. Mix the cake mix, eggs, oil, water and flavoring together. Add the coconut supreme frosting last. Pour this over the powdered sugar, coconut and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool on rack in pan 25 minutes, then turn out on cake plate.

title: kranse-kake
directions: Warm paste in double boiler; place in bowl with egg white and beat with mixer.
Gradually add sugar and beat until smooth.
Let stand in cool place overnight.
Roll on floured board into long little finger lengths and fit into molds.
Grease molds well. Bake about 30 minutes in 325°.
When baked, let stand 15 minutes, then unmold.
For decorating, use powdered sugar, water and almond flavoring.
Makes 18 rings.

title: jelly pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Mix pineapple and Jell-O together in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into oblong dish or mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix
cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and olives to garnish.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine and mix milk, lemonade, and Cool Whip.	Place in pie shell and freeze.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, lemon juice, almond extract and 7-Up. Blend.
Add flour and blend until smooth. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: deviled crab
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in bacon drippings and butter.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Put mixture in shells or casserole dish.
Brush tops with equal parts of milk and catsup.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until slightly browned around edges.

title: vegetable-beef soup
directions: *May be added during last 2 hours of cooking.

title: near perfect chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate over water and let cool.
Blend the cream cheese (softened) with sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add two egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in melted chocolate and beat smooth.
Whip cream and fold in.
Beat egg whites to soft peak, adding 1/4 cup sugar.
Gradually fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into crust and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts in skillet or on grill (best this way). In a large skillet, saute onions and mushrooms in small amount of butter until tender.
Tear cooled chicken into bite-size pieces; put in a casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cover with onions and mushrooms.
Next, cover with shredded Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted and heated thoroughly. Good served with long grain and wild rice.

title: five can casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased baking dish. Top with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in 1-inch boiling water, heat carrots and 1/4 teaspoon salt to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Drain. Add butter, sugar, nutmeg and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Return mixture to heat and cook, stirring constantly until carrots are glazed.

title: easy fried rice
directions: Cook scrambled eggs in oil.
Put in green onions, leftover meat or vegetables and rice in frying pan.
Sprinkle with soy sauce until rice is brown color.
Pepper to taste.

title: hot sausage and cheese balls
directions: Brown sausage and crumble; drain excess fat and cool sausage. Combine all ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until puffed and brown.
Cool on wire rack or paper towel.

title: tomato soup
directions: Mix and brew 1 1/2 hours.

title: sloppy joes for bazaar
directions: Add to meat mixture and mix well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 90.

title: mom's lemon fruit cake
directions: Mix all together.
Divide in half and bake 2 1/2 hours at 250° or can be baked in 1 pan.
Makes a 6 1/4 pound cake.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a large saute pan, heat oil, butter and saute onions until golden brown (10 to 15 minutes).
Sprinkle flour over onions and blend well.
Add the water and tamari or beef stock.
Add bay leaves and wine.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Before serving place one slice of toast in each bowl, sprinkle with cheese and broil just long enough to melt cheese and brown slightly (5 minutes).

title: chicken rotel casserole
directions: Boil chicken; bone and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Heat soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes in pan.
Layer chicken, soups and chips.
Top with Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: frozen pineapple yogurt
directions: In a food processor, puree the pineapple and bananas. Transfer to large bowl.
Stir in the yogurt and maple syrup. Freeze.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dirt
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with powdered sugar, pudding and Cool Whip.
Fold in Cool Whip last.
Use plastic flowerpot (put foil in bottom if pot has holes) and layer crushed cookies with cream cheese mixture.
Use cookie mixture on top so it will look like dirt.
Stick a plastic flower in pot and have fun.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Generously grease and lightly flour an 8 or 9-inch square pan. In small mixing bowl, combine eggs and sour cream.
Add 2 cups dry cake mix.
Stir by hand until well combined.
Spread about half of the batter in prepared pan.
Sprinkle about 1 cup of dry frosting mix over batter in pan.
Repeat with remaining batter and frosting mix.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: meat filled shells
directions: Cook shells according to directions on package; drain well. Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Mix meat, eggs, bread crumbs, cheese, onion, oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each shell with meat filling.
Spread thin layer of spaghetti sauce in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place shells in open side up.
Cover with rest of spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves a big family.

title: no bake banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix nuts and graham cracker crumbs. Place in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix eggs, sugar and 1 stick butter. Place on top of graham cracker mixture.
Place crushed pineapple (drained) on top of egg mixture.
Layer bananas on top of that. Cover with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Stir salt into meal. Place in a shallow dish.
Coat tomato slices in meal mix.
In large skillet, heat 1/4-inch deep oil over medium heat to 350°. Fry on one side until golden brown; turn and fry other side until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hearty cheese filling(for mexican pizza)
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly. Pour over crust.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until center is firm.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs, one at a time.
Gently fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in sifted dry ingredients. Place half of the mixture in a greased and floured Bundt cake pan. Mix cinnamon, 6 teaspoons sugar and chopped nuts together.
Top mixture in pan with half of the brown sugar mixture.
Place the remainder of the batter and top with the rest of the brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: espresso pears
directions: Stand the peeled and cored pears upright in a saucepan that will hold them snugly.
Add the coffee and enough water (about 2 cups) to cover the pears completely, then add the sugar.
Bring the coffee mixture to a boil; cover, reduce heat to low and boil gently until pears are tender, 30 minutes.
Remove the pears from the liquid and arrange them in a serving bowl.
Boil the liquid until it is reduced to 1 cup; stir in the lemon rind and pour the mixture over the pears.
Cool.
Add the Kahlua to the cooled dish and serve with cookies.

title: party chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Roll and wrap each chicken with piece of bacon.
Cover bottom of 8x12x2 baking dish with chipped beef. Mix soup with sour cream.
Arrange chicken breasts on chipped beef.
Pour soup mixture over.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: okra and tomato 1930 depression dish
directions: Saute onions and add okra. Cook until okra seems well blended (about 10 minutes). Add tomatoes.
Can use two 28 ounce cans of tomatoes. Stir in and simmer until okra is done.
(A small amount of flour can be added to thicken, if desired.)
Serve with hot corn bread.

title: red punch
directions: Mix everything together, except 7-Up.
Add last, right before serving.

title: party chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Butter baking dish and place slices of dried beef on bottom.
Wrap bacon around each piece of chicken.
Mix sour cream and soup; pour over chicken. Bake, covered, at 325° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: farmer's brownies
directions: Stir butter into cocoa and hot water; allow to cool. Sift dry ingredients together and stir into cocoa mixture. Add eggs; beat in sour milk and then vanilla. Add nuts. Spread on a greased 16 x 11-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes. When cool, top with an icing of half cocoa and half powdered sugar with 2 tablespoons of softened butter added for richness.

title: shake and bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in container and stir to combine. Prepare chicken. Put in plastic bag with ingredients.

title: kolache cookies
directions: Combine yeast, sugar, Crisco, eggs, milk and flour.
Let stand overnight.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on board and roll out a portion of the dough to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Fill with nut filling or fruit filling.
Roll up and pinch ends. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: flowerpot bread
directions: Season a 6-inch pottery flowerpot by greasing it thoroughly. Place empty into a 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Repeat.
(This prevents loaf from sticking and seals the pot.
Do not put water in the pot after it has been seasoned.)
Dissolve the yeast in water in a large mixer bowl.
Blend in ginger and 1 tablespoon sugar. Let stand in a warm place until the mixture is bubbly, about 15 minutes.
Stir in the remaining sugar, milk, salt and oil.
With the mixer on low speed, beat the flour, one cup at a time, beating very well after each addition.
Beat in the last cup of flour with a heavy spoon.
Add flour until dough is stiff, yet too sticky to knead.
Place in the flowerpot and let stand until dough rises 1 1/2 inches over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.
The top will be very brown.
Brush top lightly with butter and let cool 5 to 10 minutes, then loosen crust around the edge.

title: sweet 'n sour meatballs
directions: Melt butter in pot.
Dice onion and green pepper.
Saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except meat and cornstarch. Heat sauce for 10 minutes.
Make meatballs with ground round (like the way you would for your meatballs).
Make small ones and bake at 350° until browned.
Add cornstarch and stir until thickened.
Add meatballs.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: friendship starter
directions: Day 1:
Stir together in a large glass jar 2 1/2 cup sugar and peaches with syrup, lightly cover, and let stand at room temperature for 10 days.

title: caviar mold
directions: You will need a 7-inch spring pan.

title: pizza lasagna
directions: After beef is browned, strain grease off.
Add onion and spices.
Keep heat on medium.
Add pizza sauce and Cheddar cheese soup.
Next, pour into glass baking dish and add uncooked macaroni, mixing thoroughly.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour on 375°.

title: chicken chile
directions: In blender combine peanut oil, chili powder, garlic and peppers.
Take the 2 chickens, put in a baking dish and pour the mixture over chickens.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. When chickens are done, save pan drippings.
Pour back into blender with Dijon mustard, red wine vinegar and red onion.
Blend all together.
This makes a delicious gravy to be served with mashed potatoes.

title: mary alice's chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in bottom of pan.
Mix sour cream, mushroom soup and onion soup; spread on chicken.
Crush one roll of Ritz crackers and spread on top of soup mixture.
Dot with oleo.
Pour chicken broth over crackers, then crush another roll of Ritz crackers and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Cut crab into small pieces. Mix all of the ingredients and refrigerate in an airtight container. This is great on crackers.

title: fruited melon
directions: Cut melon in half lengthwise; remove seeds.
Scoop out melon balls, leaving shells intact.
Drain well.
Cut thin slice from bottom of each melon half to allow shells to stand upright. Divide melon balls between shells.
Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in a large bowl.
Stir in cold water.
Pour into melon shells.
Refrigerate for 3 hours, or until firm.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 8 servings.

title: white chocolate candy mix (white trash)
directions: Spread wax paper on your table and empty the pretzel sticks, Golden Grahams and halved pecans onto the wax paper; toss mixture with your (clean) hands. Melt the white almond bark according to the instructions on the package, then pour the melted white almond bark onto the mixture and continue to toss the mixture with your (clean) hands until all the pieces have coating on them. Allow the mixture to set for about 45 minutes, then break apart and enjoy.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Crumble ground beef in large glass bowl.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes on High in microwave, or until beef is browned; stir once.
Drain; stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
Cook 4 or 5 minutes on High until bubbly.

title: stockyard bean pot
directions: Drain beans, combine beans, tomatoes, and seasoning mix. Put into a 2 qt. casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes or until hot bubbly.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Freezes well before baking.
Thaw and then bake.
Serves 8.

title: the 20 minute trifle
directions: *May substitute canned fruit cocktail, drained.

title: barley casserole
directions: Saute onions and other ingredients, adding them in order. Transfer them into a deep, at least 3-quart, greased casserole dish.
Add 4 cups of water, including mushroom juice.
Bake for 2 hours at 350° or 3 1/2 hours at 225°.

title: aunt jennie's salad dressing
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add to milk in a saucepan.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and dry mustard together and stir into egg-milk mixture and mix well.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and fold in stiffly beaten (but not dry) egg whites.
Add vinegar and melted butter or oleo. Blend thoroughly; cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, oleo, eggs and bananas.
Beat with electric mixer until light and foamy. Sift together the flour, salt and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to banana mixture.
Mix well until blended. Add nutmeats.
Pour into 3 well-greased medium size loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: graham squares
directions: Mix milk and vanilla in an 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Add crumbs and chips.
Blend.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: diet pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix vanilla sugar-free pudding, pumpkin, skim milk, sweetener and spices together.
Mix according to the time on the pudding box.
Pudding sets in 5 minutes.
Pudding can also be put in a pie shell.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grind coarse through food chopper.
Add 1/2 cup chopped salted peanuts and enough Miracle Whip to stick together.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
The last 1/2 hour, add cheese.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350° covered.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Use a large bowl.
Mix all ingredients and add noodles, using just enough mayo to mix.
Serve on lettuce leaf and top with stuffed olive.

title: ritzy scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter 2-quart casserole dish.
Place one layer potatoes to cover bottom of dish.
Cover with crackers, salt, pepper and milk. Dot with butter.
Continue layering, ending with milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: spiced tea from the guardhouse
directions: Use 3 teaspoons mix per cup of hot water.

title: smoked brisket
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and rub over brisket.
Cook on grill for 3 to 4 hours or cook in oven approximately 3 hours, wrapped in foil (seal foil to keep in juices).
Bake at 300°.

title: vegetarian black bean chili
directions: Sort and clean beans.
Soak beans overnight.
Drain, cover with few inches fresh water.
Bring to boil with bay leaf.
Cook until beans are done.
Heat oil in large skillet; saute onion until soft.
Add cumin, cayenne pepper, coriander, garlic, salt and chili pepper.
Cook 5 minutes, add tomatoes in juice.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans.
Season to taste with vinegar, brown sugar and cilantro.
Serve with grated cheese or sour cream.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Combine Velveeta, salsa, mushroom soup, chicken broth and red beans.
Microwave until cheese melts.
Layer tortillas, chicken and red beans in baking dish.
Pour Velveeta sauce over top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, until hot.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Let stand 1 hour or overnight.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Put berries in 9 x 12-inch oblong dish and cover with pineapple. Pour on dry cake mix and scatter nuts over top. Melt butter and drizzle over all. Bake approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot fruit
directions: Drain juice from all cans, reserving 1 cup for sauce.
Mix together and place in greased casserole dish.
Melt margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions. Bake in two layers and cool. Split layers to make 4 cake layers.

title: cheesy hash-spinach pie
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain well, pressing out excess water.
Combine eggs, soup, flour, mustard and horseradish; stir in spinach.
Spread hash in baked shell; spoon spinach mixture over hash.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.
Combine cheese and pimento.
Spread on top of pie.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Follow directions on cake box, using milk in place of water. Prepare cake one day ahead and freeze overnight. Defrost and frost with icing.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cake mix, oleo and nuts, together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture and top with 1 1/2 sticks melted oleo and 1 cup nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush the vanilla wafers.
Add coconut and juice and mix together with your hands.
Form the mixture into 1-inch balls. Roll the balls in sugar and then refrigerate.

title: texas shrimp boil
directions: Place 1 1/2 quarts water in large boiler pot.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and return to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes until shrimp are tender.
Drain.
Serve with Rockport Red Sauce.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.	Mix soups, tomatoes and hamburger
in large saucepan.
Heat to boiling; turn off heat. Put half
of the chips in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in meat mixture; add rest of chips on top.	Cook in 350° oven for 25
to 30 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Cover with grated cheese; put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Beat egg yolks.
Add lemon juice, salt and sugar.
Cook in double boiler.
Add gelatin.
Place in vanilla wafer shell.
Beat egg whites for meringue and brown.

title: mr. leftover breakfast treat
directions: Boil eggs; cool them and dice.
Cut or separate meat into small pieces.
In a skillet, put
3 tablespoons of butter.
Melt. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add water; stir constantly.
Add meat and eggs.
Stir for approximately 2 minutes.
Serve over toast, toasted bun or English muffin.

title: salad dressing
directions: Blend sugar, oil, onion, salt and catsup in blender on high for several minutes.
Then add 1/3 cup vinegar.
Blend again. Stir in celery seed and/or mustard seed.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers.
You can also sprinkle top with grated cheese before baking.

title: double delicious halloween bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° glass).
In 13 x 9-inch pan or dish, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs evenly over butter. Pour milk over crumbs.
Press chocolate and peanut butter chips into milk layer.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned. Cool and cut into bars.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Roll out biscuits
together
until very thin.
Place on pizza pan.
Beat eggs and pour over dough.
Sprinkle meat over eggs. Salt and pepper
to
taste, then top with cheese.
Bake until brown in a 350° oven.

title: decadent ice cream dessert
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and butter, mixing well.
Press crumb mixture firmly over bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Spread 1/2 cup caramel sauce over crust, leaving 1-inch border; freeze until set.
Spread chocolate ice cream over caramel sauce; freeze until firm. Combine vanilla ice cream and crushed candy bars.
Spread mixture over chocolate ice cream; freeze until firm.
Spread 1 cup chocolate sauce over vanilla ice cream; freeze until set.
Spread coffee ice cream over chocolate sauce.
Cover tightly; freeze at least 8 hours.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving. Remove sides of spring-form pan; slice dessert into wedges.
Serve with remaining sauces.
Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Chill.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Debone chicken.
Saute onion, bell pepper and mushrooms in butter; drain.
Add cream cheese and strips of chicken.
Add filling to crescent rolls and roll up. Bake until brown.
Warm soup and Pet milk; pour over rolls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken and mushroom soup

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add margarine, sugar, flour and milk.
Beat again until blended.
Add
coconut.
Pour
into
ungreased pie plate. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces. Place white sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag. Add biscuit pieces a few at a time and shake to coat each piece.
