Place pieces in a well greased tube pan until all are used. Sprinkle layer with pecans, raisins, or coconut if desired. Bake at 450 degree for about 45 minutes. Allow to cool 15 minutes before removing from pan. Turn topside up to serve. Pieces can be pulled apart and eaten with fingers.

title: ratatouille
directions: Cook and stir onion slices in oil until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except parsley.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Uncover and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until liquid is evaporated.
Watch carefully; turn into serving dish and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings, 130 calories per serving.

title: espresso ice cream
directions: Combine the milk and coffee grounds in a saucepan.
Place over very low heat and steep for 15 minutes.
Using a fine sieve lined with cheesecloth, strain the coffeed-milk into a bowl and reserve (discard grounds).
In a mixing bowl, beat egg yolks with a wire whisk until pale yellow, then gradually beat in the sugar. Continue beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in the coffeed-milk, then the cream.

title: cheddar-ham chowder
directions: In a large kettle, bring water, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion salt and pepper to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are just tender.
Remove from heat; do not drain.

title: pumpkin cranberry bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking soda and salt.
In small mixing bowl, beat eggs; beat in sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Pour pumpkin mixture into dry ingredients. Stir just until moistened.
Stir in cranberries. Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 minutes or until wooden toothpicks comes out clean. Cool for 5 to 10 minutes. Remove from pans.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Blend both cans of tomatoes in blender or food processor. In a large pot, stir together tomatoes, beans, Pet milk, and cheese.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Add orange juice and flavorings; mix well.
Dredge fruit and nuts in flour.
Add slowly, mixing as you go until all nuts and fruit are added.

title: hamburger reuben
directions: Make 4 thin patties.
Brush with mustard.
Broil, mustard side up, approximately 5 minutes.
Turn; top with sauerkraut and slice of cheese.
Broil until bubbly.
Serve on rye toast.

title: ruby's chicken noodles
directions: In a large pot, boil chicken in 3 1/2 quarts water for 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper. Add noodles and cook until tender.

title: russian tea
directions: Put five cups water in large covered Dutch oven.
Tie cloves in small cloth and put in water; bring to a rolling boil; put in tea bags, cover and set off burner for 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags, but leave cloves in water.
Add all the juices plus the water called for in the frozen juices.
Sweeten to taste with sugar or approximately 20 (1 grain) saccharin tablets.
Put back on burner and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Do not boil.
Makes approximately 2 gallons.

title: broccoli-cheese bake
directions: Cook broccoli florets according to package directions and place in 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Stir in flour and simmer 2 or 3 minutes.
Gradually add milk and continue to heat, stirring constantly, until sauce has thickened. Add cream cheese and blend until smooth.
Remove from heat and add onions.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: incredible cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 24 to 30 cookies.

title: german-style cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in crumbs and sugar.
Pat firmly on buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package instructions.
Drain well.
In a 2 to 4-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, garlic powder and cream cheese.
Cook over low to medium heat, stirring until it is smooth and creamy.
Add drained broccoli and mix well. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes four 1/2 cup serving.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Stir together Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add pineapple and juice, coconut and nuts.
Blend together and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts and chill.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Mix all ingredients together either in a saucepan or crock-pot. Simmer for 1 hour. Serve with toothpicks. Enjoy!

title: praline cake
directions: Make cake using mix, eggs and oleo.
Bake 20 minutes in well greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni.
Place cooked macaroni, dots of margarine, cut up cheese, salt and pepper, in alternating layers in buttered 7 x 11 x 2-inch oblong baking dish.
Combine beaten eggs and milk and pour over the mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: In a small bowl, combine brown sugar, nuts, 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter. Gradually add 1 cup sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend in vanilla and lemon juice.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Pour half the batter into buttered tube pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar mixture.
Add remaining batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 3 tablespoons pineapple juice. Combine sugar and flour and stir in juice.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks.
Grease casserole dish.
Put combined ingredients in uncovered dish.
Mix crumbled crackers and margarine.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut crunches
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Add egg.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture, blend well.
Stir in coconut, oats and corn flakes.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Layer beef and Tater Tots.
Pour soup and milk over and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf and gravy
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients except 1/2 of the tomato puree and the water.
Shape mixture into a loaf.
Pour the remaining puree over the loaf and add the water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Take the meat loaf up and pour the drippings into a heavy skillet.
Make a thickening of flour and water and add slowly to the drippings until it thickens to gravy.

title: corn chowder
directions: Peel and dice potatoes, onions, celery, salt and pepper.
Add water.
Bring to boiling point, reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water, add to soup while boiling, simmer a few minutes.
Add parsley.
Add milk, cream, butter, chopped eggs, 3/4 teaspoon salt, crushed corn and whole corn and fried, diced bacon.
Heat slowly, do not boil.
Serve hot.

title: crab salad
directions: Shred crab.
Squeeze lemon over crab.
Let lemon set while you cut up celery and onion (cut up small).
Drain crab.
Add to celery, onions and seasonings.
Mix with mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Let set overnight if possible.
Best served with Waverly Wafers or Ritz crackers.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Combine cocoa, oil and water; mix well.
Add sugar, flour, buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 23 to 25 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: eva's broccoli corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, egg, salt and pepper.
Add cracker crumbs. Layer broccoli and corn mixture.
Cover with cheese.
Repeat with a layer of broccoli and corn.
Dot butter on top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: court bouillon*
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.
After each use, store remainder in freezer.
Two cups equals free food exchange.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl and set aside. In another bowl, combine buttermilk and egg; add corn and remaining ingredients.
Pour over dry ingredients and stir just until blended.
Do not overmix.
Pour batter into a greased 8 inch square pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 35 minutes or until bread tests done. Cool 5 minutes before cutting.
Serve warm or cold.
Yield:
9 servings.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream, confectioners sugar and orange extract until smooth.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; do not peel.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange slices in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish or a 9-inch pie pan.
Melt butter; stir in onion and dill weed, basil or thyme.
Drizzle over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 60 to 70 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt butter and caramels in double boiler on low heat.
With 3 pecans in each spoonful, dip into mixture, then drop onto aluminum foil sprayed with Pam.
Melt wax and chocolate in double boiler. Drop each candy in chocolate; drain, and place on foil.

title: creamed zucchini with dill
directions: Shred seeded squash (leave skin on if tender) into large bowl. Cover with cold water and add 1/4 cup salt.
Allow to soak for 15 minutes; drain thoroughly.
In Dutch oven or large heavy skillet, saute chopped onion in oil or butter; add vinegar, 1 cup water, sugar and drained squash.
Cook, covered, about 1/2 hour or until tender.
Thicken lightly with flour and water.
Add sour cream and heat, but do not boil.
Stir in dill weed to taste.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix both kinds of sugar, eggs, peanut butter and flour.
Add water slowly.
Add the vanilla in last.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix with electric mixer to blend well.
Chill.
Prepare at least one day ahead to blend flavors.
Will keep indefinitely in the refrigerator.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick and cook for 5 minutes.
Drain and layer in baking dish.
After layer of potatoes, layer with salt, pepper, margarine, bell pepper, onion and cheese.
Do this until all potatoes are used.
Top with either cream of chicken or cream of mushroom soup.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer everything in large bowl and when ready to serve add dressing.

title: raspberry jello dessert
directions: Make jello as directed and chill until partially set.
Then whip.
Whip the Pet milk.
Whip up the preserves.
Fold all together and chill.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Heat water and melt butter and chocolate squares.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Beat until of spreading consistency.
Frosts one 13 x 9-inch cake or two layer cake.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken, celery and onion in water until tender.
About one hour before you are ready to serve, mix the noodles.

title: aunt dorothy's chicken in wine sauce
directions: Skin chicken breast, flour and fry in small amount of shortening.
Remove from skillet.
Make gravy with drippings by adding 3 to 4 tablespoons flour.
Mix with drippings, then add about 1 1/2 cups of water.
Stir gravy and cook until smooth.
Chop dried beef and add to gravy, then add remaining ingredients to make sauce.
Stir until well blended.
Place fried chicken in casserole dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cook in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers, slice without peeling and soak with onions for 2 hours in the cold water in which the salt has been dissolved. Drain water.
Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard and celery seed. Add cucumbers and onions; cook until transparent.
Seal in hot jars.

title: ground chuck casserole
directions: Place meat, onion and soup in a 2 quart ungreased casserole. Mix well and place frozen Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350°F for 1-1/2 hours.

title: bologna bake
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Place in 8-inch round Ovenware cake dish.
Sprinkle with crushed potato chips. `Bake in hot oven, 400°, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pineapple-tomato-egg salad
directions: Cool eggs and push through fine sieve.
Press egg into straight sided glass or jar and refrigerate for several hours. When ready to serve, turn out carefully and slice the same thickness as pineapple.
On salad plate, arrange lettuce cups.
In center, place pineapple slice.
Atop this thick slice tomato dipped in French dressing.
Top with egg mixture.
Use French dressing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Mix noodles with all other ingredients.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle parsley on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Put dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add cottage cheese and stir.
Add drained crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Add Cool Whip and mix together.

title: dolly parton soup
directions: Boil all ingredients together until tender, then add tomatoes, dry onion soup mix, salt and pepper to taste.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add water and margarine.
Cook 8 minutes.
Serve over hot fudge cake or ice cream.

title: black bean soup
directions: Prepare dried black beans as directed, set aside. Brown hot sausage and rinse with hot tap water to remove excess grease. Chop onion, carrots, celery with tops (I add green pepper), garlic and basil.
Combine all of these ingredients with tomatoes, oregano and bay leaf in large soup kettle.
Avoid using salt if you use salted broth instead of water.
Add pepper and other favorite seasonings
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes after bringing to a boil.
Delicious with polenta or corn bread.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Peel and grate zucchini.
Mix sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla. Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Mix all together.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased bread pans at 350° about 1 hour (can be glazed).

title: frozen punch
directions: Freeze all ingredients except ginger ale in a 2-quart plastic container. One half hour before serving, remove from freezer and add ginger ale and mix.

title: quiche
directions: Fry several pieces of bacon; drain and crumble.
Butter a pie plate or a round casserole dish.
Put bacon on bottom, then 1 1/4 cups of Cheddar cheese or any kind, 1/3 cup onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Pour on top the milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper. (Blend this in blender 1 minute.)
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Cut ice cream in squares.
Dip in egg.
Cover with Team flakes or Total, crushed.
Place back in freezer.
Deep fry about 2 seconds.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or honey.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown sausage, ground beef and onion together in skillet. Drain in colander.
In large saucepan add all ingredients.
Bring to a gentle boil, then reduce heat and simmer for a couple of hours.
Stir frequently.
Freeze excess in pint containers for quick meals.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Line cupcake pans with 24 foil cupcake liners.
Place one vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fill the liner 2/3 full with cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until set.
Cool.
Top with pie filling. Chill.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in buttered baking dish.
Cover with chicken. Combine eggs, mayonnaise, onions, salt and pepper.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: southern chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler; add sugar and salt and stir.
Add 3 beaten eggs, syrup and vanilla. Mix in pecans. Pour into pie shell; bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until set and browned.

title: oatmeal-molasses ranch bread
directions: Knead on a clean surface.
Form a ball.
Put in large bowl to "rest and rise".
Knead again.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Put in greased bread pans (let rise).

title: spaghetti with fresh tomato sauce
directions: In a large saute pan, heat the oil until hot.
Add the tomatoes and saute over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add garlic and cook 30 seconds more.
In a large pot, bring water to boil.
Add pasta and 1 tablespoon of salt.
Cook pasta until tender, but still has some bite.
Remove 1 1/2 cups of the pasta cooking water and pour it over the tomatoes.
Drain pasta and transfer to a large bowl.
Bring tomato mixture to a boil.
Add the pasta, basil, salt and pepper; toss thoroughly and serve at once.
Pass the cheese separately.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake your favorite corn bread. Let cool. Hull out center and crumble in small glass dish. (Save crust for use at another time.) Mix onion, green pepper, cuke and kidney beans (undrained). Sprinkle over corn bread. Pour dressing over vegetables. Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Chill and serve.

title: gurkensalat(cucumber salad)
directions: Peel the cucumber so that a little of the green rind remains. Slice paper-thin.
Sprinkle slices with salt, sugar and vinegar. Serve this way, topped with minced parsley; or marinate in salt and sugar 15 minutes.
Drain off liquid that has accumulated. Toss with sour cream, then sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings as a relish.

title: bean salad
directions: Rinse kidney beans in cold water.
Drain all beans.
Combine all ingredients; let set overnight.
Store in refrigerator in a covered container.
Will keep 2 weeks or more.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese and cheddar cheese soften to room temperature. Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Roll mixture into ball, then roll ball in chopped walnuts.
Wrap ball in waxed paper and freeze 1/2 hour.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: In a medium mixing bowl combine the egg whites, egg, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well but not foamy.
Stir in the cooked rice, raisins and orange peel.
Pour egg mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place casserole in a baking pan; add boiling water to the baking pan to a depth of 1 inch.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until just set, stirring after 35 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled.
If desired, sprinkle with ground cinnamon.

title: elephant stew
directions: Get a big pot!
This serves 3,800 people.
Cut elephant into 1-inch cubes, frequently adding salt and pepper.
This should take approximately 72 days.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 465°.
If more than 3,800 people are to be served, two rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: chicken breasts with artichoke hearts
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute for 5 minutes until translucent.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix the cereal, sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add the oil, eggs and buttermilk to the dry mixture.
Mix well.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Dough may be refrigerated in a covered bowl for up to six weeks.
Yields 36 muffins.

title: mammy's creamed chicken on rice
directions: Boil chicken in about 2 cups of salty water for about 1 hour with lid on.
When done, cool chicken, bone and cut up chicken pieces.
Add cream of mushroom soup in broth.
(You can chill broth and skim fat if you have time.)
Add butter, chicken pieces, pimentos and a little milk.
Thicken with cornstarch mixed with water or milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over hot rice.

title: wrapped pickles
directions: Roll bread slices flat.
Spread with cream cheese.
Place pickle on bread and roll as jelly roll.
Chill.
Cut in slices.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix and put in greased crock-pot. Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix well Veg-All, soup, mayonnaise and onion.
Put into casserole dish.
Crumble 1 sleeve Ritz crackers and sprinkle over top.
Drizzle 1 stick melted butter over crackers and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grilled italian sausage
directions: Place sausage on foil.
Dice onion and pepper.
Place on top of sausage.
Pour salsa over top.
Close in foil and seal.
Grill for 1/2 hour on medium temperature.

title: charter house mud pie
directions: Crush wafers and add butter.
Mix well.
Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with soft coffee ice cream.
Put into freezer until ice cream if firm.
Top with cold fudge sauce.
Store mud pie in freezer approximately 10 hours.
Top with whipped cream and slivered almonds.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix flour and salt with sugar.
Melt butter; add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Beat eggs; add to butter and sugar, beating well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.
Thoroughly combine completely thawed berries and syrup with dry gelatin; set aside.

title: corn chowder
directions: Chop bacon and onion coarsely; put into soup kettle.
Saute until onion is soft and bacon is done.
Add potatoes, corn and water.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add butter, milk and seasonings.
Reheat to boiling.
Serve piping hot with a little parsley sprinkled over the top, or a few dashes of paprika. Makes 5 servings.

title: franks-n-ramen
directions: In an ovenproof skillet, brown frankfurters in butter.
Add onion and basil, cook until tender.
Preheat broiler.
Stir in soup, milk, tomatoes, noodles, parsley, salt and pepper; Tabasco if desired.
Heat, stirring occasionally for 4 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and place on top rack of oven. Bake until cheese just turns brown, about 4 minutes.
Remove and serve.

title: honey barbecue rub
directions: Rub each steak with 1 tablespoon honey.
Combine rest of the ingredients and rub into steaks.
Let stand 20 to 30 minutes. Barbecue or broil to desired degree of doneness.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° until done.
Do not overcook.

title: lemon-apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding mix in bowl, using package directions.
Add Eagle Brand and whipped cream; mix well.
Stir in bananas; stir in vanilla wafers.
Chill, covered, overnight.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes; put in buttered dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; dot with 1 stick butter.
Mix soup, sour cream, cheese and onion in separate bowl; pour mixture over potatoes.
Mix cornflakes and melted butter; sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk until firm.
Add vanilla extract.
Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer mixture, bananas and vanilla wafers. Set for 1 hour before serving.
Serves 12.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt butter and add all ingredients together.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan and let set.
Cut after 5 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend one at a time.
Great with fruits, especially strawberries.

title: chicken with noodles
directions: In a large pan, cook chicken with salt until tender.
Cut into cubes or shred between fingers.
Return to broth and add enough water to cook noodles according to package.
If desired, add additional salt to taste.
Also, margarine may be added for additional flavor.

title: strawberry yogurt dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Serve with fresh fruit: strawberries, kiwi slices, cantaloupe chunks, watermelon chunks, grapes and pineapple chunks.
Makes 5 cups.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery in butter.
Add catsup, sugar and Worcestershire sauce; cook slowly on low heat for 10 minutes. Add shrimp; simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: Boil for 1 minute.
Cool.
Drain vegetable mixture and add vinegar mixture.
Stir gently to mix.
Ladle into freezer containers and freeze.
Yield:
1 1/2 to 2 quarts.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Bring milk and sugar to a boil.
Mix egg yolks, vanilla and cornstarch together and add to milk and sugar mixture.
Cook until it thickens.

title: microwaved vidalia sweet onions
directions: In a medium casserole dish, cut into quarters the onions.
Cut butter into pats.
Season with salt and pepper.
Microwave on Bake setting or 70% power until onions are tender.

title: chicken and peppers(yields 4 servings; pan size: skillet)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil in skillet for 5 minutes. Add chicken.
Saute until brown on all sides.
Add basil, oregano, tomatoes, green peppers and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer, covered, for 35 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes if necessary to reduce liquid.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies until you have coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1/4 cup for top; to the rest, add margarine and mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the cream cheese with electric mixer.
Add powdered sugar; beat well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 of this on crust.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Mix pudding with milk; spread on top of cheese.
Chill for 1 hour.
Top with remaining Cool Whip; sprinkle with crumbs.
Chill well before serving.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: lo-fat strawberry salad
directions: Slice strawberries and sweeten with Sweet 'N Low.
Combine Jell-O and cottage cheese; fold in Cool Whip and sweetened strawberries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spiced nuts
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, milk, cinnamon and butter.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Add salt, vanilla and pecans.
Pour onto foil or wax paper.
Let dry, then break apart.

title: maravian ginger cookies
directions: Into 2-quart saucepan measure butter or margarine, brown sugar and molasses.
Cook over medium heat until brown sugar dissolves and butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour and remaining ingredients except sugar, until blended.
Spoon dough onto waxed paper.
Cover and refrigerate until firm enough to roll (about 2 hours).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease large cookie sheet.
On floured surface, roll 1/2 of dough into 10 x 10-inches.
Cut dough into 2 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch square.
Prick.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake.
Repeat.

title: sad cake
directions: Beat eggs well; add brown sugar and beat.
Add biscuit mix and oil mixing well.
Stir in coconut, nuts and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour in a 9 x 13 inch greased and floured baking dish. Bake at 325° until done or about 30 minutes.

title: quick cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When dissolved, add cold water.
Blend in cranberry-orange relish.
Let set in refrigerator until thickened, then add celery and nuts.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter.
Boil slowly for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, then pour over chips and marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: chicken delight
directions: Combine Homestyle veggies (including liquid), cooked, diced chicken, soup, cheese and 1 teaspoon celery seed in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, top with biscuits and sprinkle remaining celery seed on top.
Return to oven; bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, until biscuits are brown.
Serves 6.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain and put into casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix together the Bisquick, sugar, milk and add oleo.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish. Add the fruit.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes until brown.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, graham cracker crumbs and melted butter for crust.
Spread in pie plate.
Combine egg yolks, milk and lemon juice and spread in crust.
Use egg whites with 1 teaspoon sugar and whip together to form meringue; spread on top.
Bake at 350° until meringue browns lightly.
Chill and serve.
Serves 6.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat chocolate and Crisco in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Remove from heat. Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan, greased.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ground beef wellington
directions: Brown ground beef with onion soup mix.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in mushrooms, parsley, cheese and slightly beaten egg; set aside. On a floured board, roll 1/2 the dough into a 12 x 18-inch rectangle.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Place meat mixture on dough and shape into a loaf.
Roll remaining dough as directed and place on top of meat.
Seal edges securely and trim edges.
Make strips with excess dough and arrange in crisscross design on top of loaf or use cookie cutter for an attractive design.
Beat egg and milk together and brush on loaf.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage and cheese potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except sausage and potatoes.
Stir in potatoes and sausage.
Can be slow cooked in a crock-pot or oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown the meat.
Add diced veggies and seasonings; saute until blended and crisply done.
Stuff egg roll skin with mix.
Roll up and deep fry until golden brown.

title: meal in a dish
directions: Brown hamburger.
Press out all the grease.
Spread in large baking dish.
Sprinkle dry rice over this.
Salt and pepper each layer lightly.
Spoon sugar peas, juice and all, over rice.
Cover with sliced onions, then sliced potatoes and cover potatoes heavy with sliced carrots.
Mix tomato soup with water and pour over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in 400° oven. Remove foil and bake 15 minutes more.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush crackers fine.
Save 1/2 cup for topping.
Mix crackers and oleo.
Spray pan with Pam.
Line pan with crumb mix.
Press down.
Mix ice cream, pudding and milk with beater.
Spread mixture in pan and refrigerate for several hours.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle remainder of cracker crumbs on top.
Will make a 9 x 13-inch cake or 2 square 7 x 7-inch cakes.
Can be frozen.
(Cover to freeze.)

title: cracker pudding
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Beat together eggs, cornstarch and 1 cup milk.
Add this beaten mixture slowly to hot mixture.
Mixing thoroughly, bring everything to a boil.
Last, add the coconut and vanilla.
Keep refrigerated.

title: italian heritage casserole
directions: Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; arrange potatoes and pepper in bottom of dish.
Combine the seasonings; sprinkle a third of the seasoning mixture over vegetables.
Layer chicken pieces and sausage over vegetables.
Sprinkle remaining seasoning mixture on top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 375° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes more.
Yields 6 servings.

title: squash creole
directions: Lightly brown bacon; add onion.
Cook until golden.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer until just tender, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spicy glazed apricot chicken
directions: Open chili peppers and remove seeds!
Pound chicken breasts with edge of saucer to make them thinner.
Insert a strip of chili pepper (the amount is up to your taste) and a strip of cheese into each breast and roll.
Hold roll with several toothpicks.
(At this time, roll bacon around the chicken if you wish bacon, and secure with these toothpicks.)
Dip rolls into egg, then into crumbs. Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix together the flour, margarine and nuts.
Press in a 9 x 14-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool. Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar, and 2/3 of the whipped topping and pour over crust.
Prepare pudding with milk according to package directions.
Pour over filling.
Top with remainder of whipped topping and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
(Any flavor of pudding is good.)

title: best southern pancakes
directions: Stir together until mixed.
Do not overbeat.
Pour onto slightly greased, medium-hot surface and pass the butter and maple syrup!!
Yummy!

title: chicken vegetable crock-pot soup
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Mix well.
Set pot on low.
Cook soup all day; stir occasionally.
(You may want to add more broth if soup seems too dense.)
Cook egg noodles (amount is up to you) and add to soup just before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, butter, vanilla, and milk. Place in a 9 x 13 baking dish.

title: jelly doughnuts
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, butter, 1/3 cup sugar, egg yolks and salt; mix well.
Stir in enough flour to form a soft dough (do not knead).
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat juice and dissolve Jell-O.
Let cool.
Whip cream.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix and sift cocoa, flour, salt and sugar. Add unbeaten egg yolks and milk; stir well. Cook until thick. Add vanilla. Pour into baked crust. Cover with whipped cream.

title: chocolate, chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Stew meat in skillet until tender.
Brown.
Remove from skillet and make gravy.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook in salted water.
Peel and slice carrots.
Cook in salt water until tender. Slice celery and chop onions; cook together until tender.
Add all ingredients to gravy.
Add frozen peas.
Let cook for approximately 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: white cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Fold in well beaten egg whites and extract.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and frost with Chocolate Velvet Frosting.

title: creamy tuna twist
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 3 ingredients until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover.
Chill.

title: beaver with wine and shallots
directions: Cut beaver into large chunks and parboil in large kettle with water to cover.
Add whole onion, whole shallots, chopped scallions, chopped leeks, 4 cloves garlic and tarragon.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 2 1/2 hours.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until cooked. Make Stove Top according to directions on box. Cook broccoli until tender. Then layer your ingredients in a casserole dish: chicken, broccoli, Stove Top, cream of chicken or celery soup, then cheese on top. If using a large casserole dish, layer twice. Put pats of butter on the top layer of cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chinese chews
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl with rotary beater
or
electric
mixer,
beat
eggs and sugar until light and thick.
Stir in flour mixture, dates, nuts and lemon peel.
Pour into a	greased
x
9 x 1 3/4 inch baking pan. Bake at 325°
for 30 minutes until lightly brown and top is firm. Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine for 1 minute.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter and oatmeal; mix well.
Put on wax paper by spoonfuls; let set until dry.

title: beef penne pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Cook beef and onion in a large saucepan, stirring occasionally, until beef is no longer pink. Add water, tomato paste, water, bouillon; cook, stirring occasionally, for 10 to 15 minutes or until flavors are blended.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Melt butter and mix with cheese, then add all the flour, a little at a time.
Add red pepper (use more than listed if you like them hot, hot).
Add Rice Krispies and fold all ingredients together real well.
Pinch off a piece the size of a large marble and place on a cookie sheet. Mash it flat and bake in oven at 325° for about 30 minutes. Yields about 25 or 30 wafers.

title: white chip orange dream cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a small bowl.
Beat butter, sugar and brown sugar in large mixer bowl until creamy. Beat in egg and orange peel.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.
Let stand for 2 minutes.

title: green beans with tomatoes
directions: Steam green beans 5 minutes.
Heat oil in skillet.
Saute garlic, onion and beans 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes, parsley, red wine vinegar, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes more.
Chill.
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving the juice in a small saucepan.
Set pineapple aside.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups; bring to a boil.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and form into meatballs.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over meatballs in small casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Double for bigger helpings.

title: chicken bites
directions: Mix flour or pancake mix with 1/2 to 1 package (according to taste) of Italian salad dressing mix.
Dip chicken bites into egg and roll in flour or pancake mixture.
Place on paper towel until all are rolled.
Deep fry in hot vegetable oil until golden brown.

title: rosy apple whirls
directions: Bring 1 1/2 cups sugar, water and candies to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour into a 12 x 18 x 2-inch pan, reserving 1/2 cup for topping. Sift the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Cut in shortening thoroughly until particles are fine.
Break egg into measuring cup and add enough milk to measure 2/3 cup.
Beat with a fork to combine. Add to dry ingredients all at once.
Stir until dough clings together in a ball.
Knead lightly on floured board 12 to 15 strokes.
Roll out to a 12-inch square.
Spread with 1 tablespoon melted butter. Cover with the apples. Roll as for a jelly roll. Cut into 8 (1 1/2-inch) slices and place on syrup in pan.

Bake in moderately hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes. Spoon reserved syrup over biscuits, 1 tablespoon on each, and continue baking 10 or 15 minutes longer until golden brown. Serve warm with plain or whipped cream.

title: peachy cinnamon coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Drain peaches, reserving juice.
Add water to reserved juice to equal 3/4 cup liquid.
Chop peaches.
Combine muffin mix, egg and 3/4 cup peach liquid in medium bowl.
Fold in peaches.
Pour into pan. Knead swirl packet from mix 10 seconds before opening.
Squeeze contents on top of batter and swirl with a knife.
Sprinkle contents of topping from mix over batter.
Bake at 400° for 28 minutes for 8-inch pan or 20 to 25 minutes or 9-inch pan.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix 1 teaspoon cinnamon with 1/2 cup sugar.
Cream oleo, 1 cup sugar and eggs together.
Add sour cream, vanilla, flour, baking powder and soda.
Layer half of batter in pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and add chocolate chips.
Spread with rest of batter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: all-at-once spaghetti
directions: Heat oil in deep pot or skillet.
Add onion, cook until soft. Crumble in beef.
Stir and fry until meat loses red color. Sprinkle salt and pepper over.
Pour in tomato sauce and water; bring to boil.
Break spaghetti in half.
Sprinkle in a little at a time, stirring it into sauce to keep it separated.
Cover tightly and stir occasionally.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with cheese.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: crawfish or shrimp dip
directions: Boil crawfish tails (shrimp) just long enough to turn red. Chop green onions and parsley.
Drain crawfish or shrimp.
Mix cream cheese until soft.
Add crawfish (shrimp), green onions and parsley, then mix well.
Then add salt and Tabasco to taste. Cover to refrigerate until cream cheese is firm.
Then serve.
Can do ahead.

title: strawberry meringue torte
directions: Combine graham crackers, sugar, margarine and pecans; press into bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Slice enough berries to make 2 cups.
Combine in large bowl with sugar, egg whites, lemon juice, vanilla and salt. Beat on low speed to blend, then high speed until firm peaks form, about 15 minutes.
Fold whipped cream into berry mixture.
Pour into cold baked crust.
Cover and freeze until very firm.
To serve, remove pan sides, arrange rest of berries on top or sides.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Coarsely chop cabbage, bell pepper and onion in food processor.
Add remaining ingredients and pour over slaw.
Cover and refrigerate.
This salad will keep up to 3 days in the refrigerator.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, pepper, soup and 1/2 can onions in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake for 5 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cake mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.	Sprinkle a little powdered sugar over baked cake as soon as it is done.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: cheesy pizza dinner
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Stir in remaining ingredients and beat thoroughly.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain and flake salmon and place into mixing bowl.
Add eggs and mix with a fork.
Add crumbled crackers and mix well.
Make small to medium patties and place in a preheated skillet.
Fry on each side 3 to 4 minutes until done.

title: oven pancake(finnish pancake)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt well.
Add half of the milk and beat again.
Add all of the flour and remaining milk.
Melt 1/3 cup butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into the heated and buttered pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400° and finish baking for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar immediately after removing from oven.
Serve with fresh berries, peaches or apricots.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Place chocolate squares and butter in small heavy skillet. Melt chocolate over low flame.
In mixing bowl, combine sugar and cream. Add to melted chocolate.
Stir over medium-low flame until sauce reaches boiling point.
Reduce heat.
Cook over low flame until sauce thickens slightly.
Stir in vanilla. Serve hot or cold over ice cream.

title: chicken with dried beef
directions: Baking Temperature: 275°.
Baking Time: 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: pat's sausage cornbread
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain well.
Combine eggs, cornmeal, corn, milk and vegetable oil.
Pour half of mixture into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with sausage mixture and grated cheese.
Pour remaining batter over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven to cool 10 minutes before serving.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: **springerli
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, beat 15 minutes.
Add flour and baking powder sifted 3 times.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Then roll with printed roller or press with printed board.
Cut, place on greased cookie sheet sprinkled with anise seed.
Let stand 2 hours in warm place, bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 9 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions and carrots in small amount of salted water until tender; drain.
Combine cooked vegetables with sour cream, cream of chicken soup and pimentos.
Add butter to herb dressing.
Layer squash mixture alternately with dressing, beginning and ending with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: albondingas soup
directions: In medium bowl, combine beef, crumbs, minced onion, water, eggs, salt and 1/4 teaspoon Tabasco sauce.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Cover and refrigerate.
Coarsely chop enough green pepper to yield 1/2 cup.
Cut remainder into thin strips for garnish.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Add ingredients together, one at a time, in order given. Grease and flour a tube pan.
Spread batter evenly in pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, flour and salt, which has been mixed together and stir until it begins to thicken.
Beat egg yolks in cup and add 1/2 cup of hot pudding; stir well and add slowly to mixture.
Add vanilla and butter.
Remove from fire.
Pour 1/2 of pie filling in baked crust; spread pineapple on, then cover with remaining filling.
Cover with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: fruited pork roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place roast in pan. Arrange onions, apples and raisins around meat.
Sprinkle
all ingredients with seasonings.
Bake, uncovered, 2 hours.
After 1 hour, place baking potatoes on shelf, if you wish, or acorn squash, if in season.

title: steak and dressing
directions: Place steak on large sheet of aluminum foil and salt and pepper to taste.
In large bowl, place dressing mix, soup mix and pour melted margarine over it.
Stir and add enough water to make dressing damp, but not soupy.
Place dressing on half of the steak and fold the other half over top.
Fold and seal foil around the meat and place in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
About 15 minutes before meat is done, pour mushroom soup in bowl and beat with a fork until smooth.
Pour over meat and return to oven, leaving the foil open.
Heat until the soup is hot and bubbling.

title: lemon lush("sugar-free")
directions: Mix well.
Spray bottom only of 9 x 13 pan with Pam.
Press mixture onto pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese keigel
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix noodles, 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese and pepper in large bowl.
Place cream cheese, cottage cheese and eggs in blender or food processor fitted with steel blade.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Add to noodle mixture; mix lightly.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: alberta's dumplings
directions: Mixture should be thinner than pie dough; drop by teaspoon into boiling salt water.
Cook 10 minutes without lid, 10 minutes with lid.
Add sauteed onions and butter or put your favorite gravy on them.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: hearty sausage soup
directions: Melt butter in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Saute onion until tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir in flour and seasonings until smooth.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in milk and broth. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add potatoes, lima beans and sausage.
Heat all these ingredients thoroughly and serve.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: In a small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over water.
Let stand 3 minutes to soften. Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved.
In food processor or blender, combine gelatin mixture and remaining ingredients except crust and topping.
Process until well blended.
Pour into crust.
Cover and chill several hours. Top with whipped topping.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in large skillet; cover and simmer for 30 minutes until tender.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches; reserve syrup.
Mix with other ingredients. Bring to boil; lower temperature and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour hot syrup over peaches.
Add maraschino cherries if desired (makes it pretty).
Cool; chill in the refrigerator before serving.
A good dish to prepare a day or so before serving.
Good served with turkey, ham or roast.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix in mushrooms, spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Spread mixture in a 7 x 11-inch pan. Mix soup and Mozzarella cheese together; spread over meat mixture. Unroll crescent rolls; leave in 2 rectangles.
Lay over soup mixture.
Drizzle with butter, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Place in greased casserole dish. Top with cheese.
Mix cracker crumbs with soft butter and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix mayo, cheese and soup.
Add to broccoli. Pour in baking dish. Brown crackers and margarine on top of stove. Pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with cornbread mix.
Divide in half.
Mix half with squash and other ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Top with remaining crumbs and bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: brown's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, cook filling until thick.
Cool and pour into cooked pie shell.
Top with margarine or whipped cream.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Soak cornbread and biscuit pieces in 4 cups broth. Melt margarine. Add celery and onion; cook until tender. Add with eggs to cornbread mixture. Add 4 cups broth and seasonings; mix well. Bake in a shallow uncovered pan at 325° for 1 hour. Makes 12 cups.

title: california casserole
directions: Brown meat in oil in skillet.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole (leave drippings in skillet).
In drippings, cook onion and green pepper until limp and brown.
Leave drippings and spoon vegetables over meat in casserole.
In skillet, cook and stir rice until light brown.
Stir rice, seasonings and olives into meat and vegetables.
Blend water and tomato paste; pour over meat mixture. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: zucchini cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Add nuts. Stir and pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or 3 round pans.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Saute onions, green pepper and celery.
Stir soup and water until creamy.
Mix all ingredients and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese melts.

title: bleu and cottage cheese salad dressing
directions: Blend cottage cheese and sour cream.
Blend all remaining ingredients and add to cottage cheese mixture.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pork chops 'n' rice
directions: In a large glass dish, pour rice on bottom.
Put pork chops on top of rice.
Pour soups and water over meat and rice.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(May also be used with chicken breast.)

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Use 1/4 to 1/3 cup of the mixture per 1 cup boiling water and stir well.

title: hungarian cabbage rolls
directions: Cut core from cabbage, put in large pot of boiling water. Cook 10 minutes.
Remove and let stand 10 to 15 minutes to soften leaves.
Mix together ground beef, onion (minced), rice, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Separate cabbage leaves carefully. Place on a leaf on board, put a spoonful of meat mixture at base of leaf, roll up loosely to permit swelling of rice.

title: crock-pot barbecued chicken
directions: Warm crock-pot with water.
Dump water.
Put 1/4 cup barbecue sauce in pot.
Place a layer of chicken pieces in pot.
Salt chicken and cover with sauce.
Place another layer of chicken, salt and sauce as before.
Cook until tender.

title: deep fried fish
directions: Heat oil in a frying pan on high heat.
Mix flour, salt, seasoning salt and Accent in a Ziploc bag.
Then place some of the fish with mixture and shake.
Finally, take out floured fish and place them in hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, or light brown. Last, when done, take out and place in bowl.
(Repeat process until all of fish is done.)

title: coconut bars
directions: Sift together white sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs.
Pour in brown sugar and stir until all the lumps dissolve.
Add nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Stir well again.
Pour into a greased baking pan and bake for about 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into bars and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: halupki for beginners
directions: Chop onion finely and saute in olive oil.
Add paprika; set aside.
Parboil whole head of cabbage (from which core has been removed) until leaves are just transparent, but not too soft.
(If leaves are too soft, they will tear when rolled.)
Remove leaves one at a time as they are blanched.
If section close to the core end is too thick, pare some off with a thin knife.
Set leaves aside.
Mix together pork, steak, rice, salt, pepper, catsup and water and onion mixture.
(Add one egg, if desired, not necessary.)
Take a cabbage leaf and place a small handful of the meat mixture in the center of it.
Fold over one side, then roll the cabbage completely over the meat.
Tuck the remaining end cabbage in by pushing your finger into it.
If too much cabbage is left on the end, trim it off.
Arrange cut-up cabbage on the bottom of a large pot (10 or 12-quart) and arrange cabbage rolls on it in layers.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Put rinsed sauerkraut on top.
Add water to cover completely.
Cover with lid and bring to a boil over medium heat.
After it boils, simmer for 2 hours.
Makes about 36 cabbage rolls.
(The leaner the meat, the more dry the rolls will be.)

title: low-fat chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, margarine, Egg Beaters and vanilla. Add flour and mix until thoroughly blended.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Press 4 to 5 chocolate chips into each dough ball.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields about 6 dozen cookies.

title: fruit and pimento cheese salad
directions: Whip the cream. Stir in softened cheese, salad dressing, vanilla and sugar. Fold in fruit and marshmallows. Chill well.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, add apples and grapes.
Add sugar with cranberries, mix remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: pancake-sausage wedges
directions: Place sausage, spoke-fashion, in lightly greased 9-inch quiche dish.
Combine flour, eggs, milk and oil, stirring until moist. Spoon over sausages.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 12 servings.
Top with butter and syrup.

title: sugar-free peanut butter pie
directions: Bake pie crusts and set aside.
With 3 cups milk and 1 pudding mix, cook as directed and add 1/4 cup peanut butter.
Mix well and pour 1/2 into each crust.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Cover corned beef brisket with boiling water.
Simmer (do not boil) for 3 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.
Add cabbage, potatoes and onion.
Simmer about 1/2 hour longer, or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Let stand about 10 minutes.

title: shilo salad
directions: Bring last 5 ingredients to a boil, then add sweetener.
Pour over vegetables and chill overnight.

title: broccoli casserole(yields 4 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a shallow 1-quart baking dish. Melt butter in a medium sized saucepan.
Add onion and garlic. Cook for about 4 minutes until translucent.

title: apricot fig loaf
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl.
Add dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten.
Pour into 3 small greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven and cool in pans, 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and continue cooling.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Prepare a 9-inch baked pie shell; cool.
Mash enough berries to measure 1 cup.
Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water and crushed berries.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in a few drops of red food color; cool. Beat the cream cheese until smooth; spread on bottom of cooled baked pie shell.
Fill shell with remaining berries.
Pour berry mixture over top.
Chill at least 3 hours, or until set.

title: pecan cobbler
directions: Mix eggs, 3/4 c. sugar, syrup, 2 tbsp. melted butter, 2 tbsp. flour, salt and pecans together and set aside.

title: simple microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine all but 1/4 cup of ketchup in large mixing bowl.
Mix well with hands and form a firm round loaf. Use glass or microwavesafe round casserole dish or similar.
Place loaf in dish and spread remaining 1/4 cup ketchup on top of meat loaf. Microwave on High, uncovered, for 21 minutes or until done, rotating plate after 7 minutes.

title: low-fat lemon chicken
directions: In a large skillet, combine lemon juice, mustard, garlic powder, pepper, orange juice, broth mix, parsley and vegetable oil.
Heat over medium heat until hot.
Add chicken.
Turning frequently, cook chicken until done (about 15 minutes).
Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 10 more minutes.

title: sausage and tomatoes
directions: Brown sausage.
Pour tomatoes, tomato sauce and onion over drained sausage.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: bok choy salad
directions: Saute until golden brown. Put in sealed container.

title: chocolate pies (3)
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together. Mix cocoa and flour together and add to first mixture. Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Lower to 325° for 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned gingersnaps
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the margarine and sugar.
Add egg and molasses; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Chill the dough.
Roll into 1 1/4-inch balls and dip into sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until set and surface cracks.
Cool on wire racks.
Yield: about 4 dozen.

title: caesar dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in food processor or blender and mix together.
After blended, pour on top of 1 1/2 to 2 heads of fresh crisp romaine lettuce.

title: danish apple cake
directions: *Crush zwieback with a rolling pin to make fine crumbs.
Makes 2 cups crumbs.

title: surprise muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of muffin cups.

title: vegetable filled flounder
directions: In the microwave, cook mushrooms, pepper and sliced green onion until soft.
Stir in garlic, parsley and basil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cut four 12-inch lengths of aluminum foil.
Spray foil with vegetable spray.

title: peach angel pie
directions: Beat together egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in 1 cup of the coconut and the nuts. Spread in a well buttered 9-inch pie plate, building up the sides.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until
lightly browned.
Cool.

title: caramel balls
directions: Melt margarine, caramels and milk over low heat; stir until caramels melt.
Add coconut and nuts.
Add crushed corn flakes. Drop by tablespoons on wax paper; let cool 1 hour.
Put in tight container.

title: reception salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and juice from pineapple (about 2 cups in all). Chill. Mash pimientos (drained) with cream cheese. Add pineapple, celery and nuts. When jello has started to thicken, fold in cream cheese mixture and whipped cream. Pour into a sheet cake pan or mold. Chill until firm. Garnish with cherries.

title: cheese snack cracker
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Cut in margarine with fork to crumb size.
Add vinegar, cheese and cold water.
Mix and shape into ball; wrap in wax paper or plastic.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Roll out amount needed (store rest in refrigerator).
Roll very thin, cut in wedges, bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Done when you stick butter knife in center and it comes out clean.

title: rich chocolate icing(this chocolate icing is easy to make.)
directions: Combine, in a double boiler, the sugar, salt, cornstarch and chocolate.
Add boiling water and cook until thick.
Remove from heat, stir in butter and vanilla and beat well.
Let cool, then spread on cake.

title: chicken kabobs
directions: Preheat oven to broil.
Remove excess fat from boneless chicken breast.
Cube chicken breast and season.
Spray kabob stick with vegetable spray.

Starting and ending with the cherry tomatoes, you can thread the vegetables on the kabob stick however you prefer. Place in broiler and cook for 10 minutes; turn and cook for an additional 10 minutes.
When golden brown, they are ready to serve. Can be served over rice or pasta.

title: quick rolls
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients and add 1 cup flour.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Stir down and add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Stir and knead for 3 minutes.
Roll in a ball.
Put in a greased pan; let rise for 25 minutes.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: rice-chicken casserole
directions: Spread rice on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with soup mix.
Mix soups and water together and pour over rice. Top with chicken and cut up sticks of oleo over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Beat the sour cream, mayonnaise, salt and lemon juice to make dressing.
Toss chicken, celery and mushrooms together with dressing to coat evenly.
Chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, add pecans, bacon and scallions.

title: butterscotch fingers
directions: Mix well
and
bake
in
a square cake pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Cut in the center and then in strips.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill several hours to let flavors blend.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: orange cake
directions: Bring to a boil. Pour over hot baked cake.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix oil, cocoa and sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in salt, flour and baking powder. Chill several hours or overnight.
Drop teaspoon of dough into confectioners sugar.
Roll around and shape into a ball.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: honey pork and rice sunday rest meal
directions: Broil pork for 10 to 15 minutes, drain well.
Combine ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours or on high 3 to 4 hours.
Remove pork.
Add 1 1/2 cups rice.
Cook until done.

title: boomba poliuka spanielska
directions: Combine all ingredients except macaroni in a saucepan.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Add cooked macaroni and heat a few minutes longer. Top each serving with additional cheese. Best if made early in the day and reheated.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and sugar together until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Mix oats and raisins; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Store in airtight container.

title: orange-pineapple punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in frozen pineapple and orange juice.
Add 3 cups cold water.
Slowly add ginger ale and pineapple juice.
Stir well.

title: herb biscuit ring
directions: Melt butter.
Add lemon juice and spices.
Roll biscuits in herb butter.
Put in round cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender and debone.
Heat oil and saute onions and pepper and celery.
Mix all ingredients except spaghetti into large pot to melt cheese.
Add cooked spaghetti.
Pour into large casserole dish (9 x 13).
Bake 30 minutes at 250°.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Cut off and discard tough ends of broccoli stalks. Cut tops into small flowerets; slice stalks 1/4-inch thick. Set aside.

title: crock-pot lasagna
directions: Stir all together in crock-pot.
Add 1 cup of water.
Cook on high for 30 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese on top.
Cook on low for 3 hours or until noodles are soft.

title: pollo al chilindron
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in flour seasoned with salt and pepper. Heat olive oil and add garlic; remove when browned.
Brown chicken.
Add ham and onion.
Cook until onion is golden.
Add the peppers and cook over medium to low heat until tender.
Add the tomatoes and cook over low heat until the chicken is cooked through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pan-fried sweet potatoes with canadian bacon
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, peel and cut sweet potatoes into 3/4-inch thick slices. Dice onion.

In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon hot salad oil, cook onion until tender; remove to large bowl. In the same skillet over medium heat, in 3 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook sweet potatoes until golden brown on one side.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 5 minutes. With pancake turner, turn potatoes.
Cook over medium heat until browned on the other side. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes longer until potatoes are tender.
Remove sweet potatoes to bowl with onion.

title: almond apple cake(blue ribbon recipe)
directions: Grease well and flour an angel food pan.
In mixer, blend 1/2 cup butter with 1 cup sugar.
Add egg and almond flavoring.
Blend in flour, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Chill batter well. Press into bottom and up sides about 2 to 3 inches.
Flour fingers to help, as batter is sticky.
Peel apples; use hand grater, shredder side.
Slice right into pan.
Apples can also be chopped. Sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: monster toast
directions: With cookie cutters, cut monster shapes out of bread slices or make a paper pattern and cut out monsters with kitchen scissors. Dip each cut-out into concentrated orange juice.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 250° oven until lightly toasted, about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; fold in sugar.
Chop crackers in blender; chop nuts in blender.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Ice with whipped cream.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken for 30 minutes in the oven at 350°.
Boil rice. Add to chicken.
Then add soups over chicken and rice.
Cook another 30 minutes, covered, or until done.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Put 1/2 cup catsup and 1/4 cup brown sugar in a pan.
Stir together and simmer.
Combine with bacon and onions.
Put green beans in a casserole dish.
Pour mixture of catsup, brown sugar, onions and bits of bacon over beans.
DO NOT STIR.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir and bring to a boil the white and brown sugar, evaporated milk and margarine.
Bring to a soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter. Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into a greased pan. When cool, cut into squares.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix thoroughly; let stand 2 to 3 minutes.
Drop onto pan (sprayed with Pam).
Flatten a little.
Bake 20 minutes at 325° until lightly brown.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine and pour into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken and seafood rice(paella a la valenciana)
directions: Heat the broth with the saffron and simmer 15 minutes.
Cut the chicken into small serving pieces, the whole breast in 4 parts. Sprinkle with salt.
In a metal paella pan, with about a 15-inch base, heat the oil.
Add the chicken pieces and fry over high heat until golden.
Remove to a warm platter.
Add the chorizo, pork and ham to the pan and stir-fry about 10 minutes.
Add the chopped onion, scallions, garlic and pimientos and saute until the onion is wilted.
Add the shrimp and the lobster and saute about 3 minutes more or until the shrimp and lobster barely turn pink (the lobster will cook more in the oven).
Remove the shrimp and lobster to the platter with the chicken.
Add the rice to the pan and stir to coat it well with the oil.
Sprinkle in the 5 tablespoons chopped parsley and the bay leaf.
Stir in the chicken broth, boiling the wine, lemon juice and peas.

title: crab bisque
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan; stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk and bouillon gradually.
Cook, stirring over low heat until thickened.
Add crab meat, onion and parsley.
Cover and simmer over low heat 10 minutes.
Add cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana punch
directions: Heat water to dissolve juices.
Add all ingredients.
Add Sprite or 7-Up.
Serve.

title: vasa mazue
directions: Boil noodles; drain.
Add sausage, seasoning, tomatoes and sliced or diced onion.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sausage and bean soup
directions: Brown turkey and bacon in skillet.
Add tomatoes, water, bouillon cubes; bring to a boil.
Add macaroni and kidney beans. Simmer until macaroni is cooked.

title: good potatoes
directions: Shred potatoes.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole at 350°
for 25 minutes.

title: easy m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix, eggs and oil in a large bowl until mix is dissolved.
Mix M&M's into dough. Drop balls of dough onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 9 to 12 minutes until golden brown. Remove from pan and cool.

title: st. luke's hot dish
directions: Brown meat, onion, pimento in frying pan.
Cook noodles until tender.
Mix everything together.
Put in casserole and bake for 1 hour.
Other leftover meat may also be used.
If using poultry, use cream of chicken soup instead of cream of celery.
Put crumbs or French dried onions on top of casserole.

title: turkey sage meat loaf
directions: Mix in order given and place in Pam sprayed loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Serve with sweet peas, baked potatoes, green beans, coleslaw and rolls. Makes 4 to 5 servings meat loaf.

title: sauteed green beans - herbs(serves 4)
directions: Cut the green beans into 2-inch lengths.
In a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, warm oil until hot but not smoking. Add onion and garlic; saute for 30 seconds.
Add the beans, basil, oregano, salt and peppers; saute until the beans are tender but still crisp, 3 to 5 minutes.

title: microwave mexi dip
directions: In a glass pie pan, spread cream cheese.
Pour chili over that, then salsa.
Sprinkle with package of cheese and slice a few olives on top.
Put in microwave for 10 minutes.
Dip with your favorite chip.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Line casserole with 1/2 asparagus.
Sprinkle with 1/2 crushed crackers.
Mix soup with milk; pour 1/2 mixture over crumbs. Repeat and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cover with cheese and melt.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: In a bowl or gallon size Baggie, mix together salad oil, Ranch dressing mix, dill weed, lemon pepper and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Pour crackers into mixture and blend, just coating the crackers.
Bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Great for children in cars.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute margarine, onion and green pepper until soft.
Set aside. In a large bowl, mix well the corn, muffin mix and eggs.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the sauteed mix over top of corn mix. Spoon sour cream in chunks on top of onion sauteed mix.
Just before baking, spread top with grated sharp cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mock cheese blintzes
directions: Cut crusts off bread.
With rolling pin, roll out very thin. Whip with mixer cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and egg yolks until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture on bread.
Gently roll up like a jelly roll.
Melt butter.
Mix 1 cup sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg together in small mixing bowl.
Dip rolled breads into melted butter.
Roll in cinnamon mixture.
Place in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Place in freezer for at least 4 hours.
Take out of freezer 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: calico potato salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together in salad bowl. Toss lightly, then add dressing.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients except bread in a bowl.
In a small bowl of cool water, dip each piece of bread separately.
Gently squeeze water from bread, leaving it moist.
Break the bread mixture into the meat mixture. Roll into loaf and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes, until evenly browned.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato sauce, together by hand in a large bowl.
Form into meatballs, about 1 inch in diameter.
Fry meatballs in skillet until brown on all sides.
Add tomato sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook on low 30 minutes. Great served over mashed potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken a l'mandarin
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and mandarin juice. Coat chicken pieces with marinade and refrigerate 30 minutes or overnight.
Remove chicken from marinade and place in baking dish. Bake for 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
Reduce heat to 300°, continue baking, turning chicken, basting with marinade.
Bake until chicken is done, about 20 minutes.
Five minutes before removing from oven, pour mandarin juice over chicken.
Serve marinade and drippings from pan in a separate bowl.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tim's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter with sugar; beat in rest of ingredients.
Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: oatmeal cookies with almonds
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
When hot, scatter the oats and almonds on a baking sheet and place in the oven for 5 to 6 minutes or until nuts are lightly toasted.
Beat egg and sugar in a mixing bowl for 2 minutes, until mixture is light colored.
Gradually stir in the oil, keeping the batter smooth, then the skim milk.
Now the remaining ingredients.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook to heat and it is ready to seal in jars.
(I like to make my own applesauce by quartering and coring apples, leave peels on.
Cook until tender then blend in blender and its ready to make apple butter.)

title: basic white sauce
directions: *Thirteen ounces of canned milk may be substituted.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tiger butter (candy)
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter.
Pour onto foil-lined cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips.
Drizzle over almond bark mixture.
Swirl with spoon or knife.
Chill until hard, then break into pieces.

title: quick strawberry short cake
directions: Cut cake into three layers.
Clean and mash half of the strawberries then stir in the powdered sugar.
On the bottom layer of cake, spread strawberry mixture then Cool Whip.
Then layer until the top.
Cut the rest of the strawberries to decorate the top.
Keep cool.

title: corn bake
directions: Pour in casserole and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon rolls in food processor
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix egg and vanilla and enough warm water to make 3/4 cup.
Turn on and blend until a ball forms. Turn onto floured surface and knead until firm.
Turn into greased bowl; cover and let rise.
Roll out dough.
Spread margarine over it.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/4 cup white sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon and sprinkle over top.
Raisins may be added.
Roll up and cut into pieces.
Place onto baking sheet. Let rise.
Bake in a 350° oven until light brown.

title: chocolate jumbos
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Do not chill.
Roll thick on well floured board.
Cut in desired shapes or traditional donut circles.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost.

title: apple bread
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and milk.
Mix flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Gradually add to egg mixture; blend well.
Fold in nuts, apples and raisins.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: celery-dill shaker seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 3 1/2 tablespoons.
Less than 1 mg sodium per teaspoon.

title: maduro en gloria (ripe plantains in heavens)
directions: Cut plantains in slanted slices and fry in hot oil until they are golden.
Mix the sugar, cornstarch and ground cinnamon; add milk, shredded cheese and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Grease a Pyrex dish with 1/2 tablespoon of butter.
Pour in half of milk mixture and other ingredients.
Place fried slices of plantain on top.
Cover with remaining milk mixture and dot with butter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is just melted.

title: potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: frozen everready waldorf salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice, lemon juice, sugar, beaten eggs and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool (setting pan in larger pan of ice water helps).
Add celery, diced apples and pineapple.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Put in suitable dishes for freezing; 2 (8 x 10-inches) work.
Cover well with plastic wrap and foil to seal.

title: paul vonfuw's soft rolls
directions: Crumble yeast over milk.
(If you use dry yeast, dissolve 2 packages in 1/2 cup warm water; decrease milk to 1 1/2 cups.) Stir to combine.
Add sugar, eggs, salt and oleo.
Add four cups flour, beating until smooth.
Add remainder of flour until firm dough is formed.
Knead thoroughly.
Grease and place in bowl. Cover with damp towel.
Let rise in warm place (80°) until doubled in bulk (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down and let rest 10 minutes. Dough is now ready for shaping into rolls.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: jumbo chocolate raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat all ingredients, except chocolate pieces, nuts and raisins until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients with spoon.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine bread crumbs, onions, ketchup, egg, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Add meat, mix well but do not overmix.
Shape into oval patties 1/2-inch thick.
Broil under preheated hot broiler until done as desired, about 4 to 5 minutes on each side.
Makes 6 portions.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes in jackets. Refrigerate until cool enough to peel and grate in baking dish. Salt and pepper to taste.
In saucepan, melt the other ingredients and pour over the potatoes. Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian ham sandwich
directions: Slice bread horizontally. Remove top. Layer ham and cheese. Replace top. Wrap entire loaf in foil. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Unwrap and cut into wedges. Serve with soup.

title: aunt virginia's toffee
