directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In saucepan, heat brown sugar, margarine and butter to boiling. Cover over medium/low heat for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in nuts.

title: tofu burger loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate-dipped strawberries
directions: In a double boiler, combine the chocolate, butter and cognac over moderate heat.
Melt the mixture, stirring frequently until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: blender chocolate pie
directions: Put half of milk in blender; put rest of ingredients except vanilla.
Add the other half cup of milk.
Blend well.
While blending, let a heavy skillet warm over medium heat.
Pour into skillet and start stirring constantly.
Let come to a boil; take from heat.
Add vanilla and pour into cooked pie shell.
Before beating egg whites, add 1 tablespoon cold water and a pinch of salt.
Start beating, add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Spread on cooled pie.
Brown at 375° for 10 minutes.
Chill.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese, eggs, chives and oregano; set aside. Brown and drain ground chuck.
Add mushrooms and spaghetti sauce and cook at least 20 minutes on low.
Layer sauce, lasagna noodles (uncooked), Ricotta cheese mixture and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.

title: seasoned green beans
directions: Drain juice from beans into a measuring cup.
Stir-fry beans for 1 minute.
Add onion and stir-fry until onion is tender.
Add juice, garlic and almonds.
Cover and cook on medium until garlic is tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: 5 minute pizza dough
directions: Mix dry yeast with cup of warm water.
Add teaspoon salt, sugar and cooking oil.
Stir well.
Add flour and mix well with spoon until flour is absorbed with other ingredients.
Place bowl in a warm place (on top of pilot light on stove).
Let dough rise for 5 to 10 minutes.

While dough is rising, open a small can of tomato sauce or pizza sauce, grate cheese of your preference and prepare other extras you would like to add such as mushrooms, onions, pepperoni, sausage, etc.
Smooth a small amount of oil on pizza pan.
Take dough and spread evenly on oiled pan.
Place tomato sauce evenly with spoon on dough.
Add cheese and other ingredients.
Place in oven at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes. (I check the bottom of pizza with a utensil to see if crust is brown enough.)
Do not burn.

title: mock hasenpfeffer
directions: Combine flour, basil, salt and pepper and rub well into the rabbit pieces.
Heat the oil and saute the rabbit until it browns lightly.

title: spaghetti a la hazel
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in oil until tender.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add next 4 ingredients and simmer at least 1 hour.
(Add more water as necessary.)
Put sauce and cooked spaghetti together.
Add grated cheese on top (Parmesan or American).
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender and drain.
Saute the onion and green pepper in the margarine until it is browned.
Combine spaghetti, onion mixture, soup, chicken, pimentos and 1 cup cheese. Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with the other cup of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: basic milkshake
directions: The combination of syrup and ice cream is up to you!

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Pour off any grease.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes over medium heat, uncovered. Add soup and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and cooked noodles.
(Adjust quantity to personal taste.) Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: blueberry bake
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, buttered, place 1/2 of cubes.
Spoon Mascarpone cheese.
Sprinkle blueberries.
Then add rest of bread cubes, mixed eggs, milk and syrup.
Pour over.
Chill overnight. Bake 350° covered with foil for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: In a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish layer 8 bread slice halves, the cheese slices, then the remaining bread slice halves. Beat eggs.
Stir in milk, onion, mustard, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Pour over bread and cheese layers.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator for 2 to 24 hours.
Bake uncovered in a 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until set and lightly browned.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: grape butter
directions: Boil for 20 minutes; put through colander and can.

title: old fashioned tea cakes(over 100 years old)
directions: Beat egg yolks, soft shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and milk.
When dough is stiff enough to roll out, fold in 2 beaten egg whites.
Turn out on floured board.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter or glass.
Bake at 375°.
Cook until slightly brown.

title: barbe cups
directions: Put biscuits in muffin tins.
Press up on sides.
Brown ground beef and drain. Add onion and barbecue sauce.
Pour even amounts in each biscuit.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spiced devil's food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9-inch layer cake pans, dusting lightly with cocoa or flour.

title: crunchy fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate together over low heat.
Combine eggs and sugars.
Add chocolate mixture, flour, salt, vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Bake in greased 9-inch pie plate, or use a graham cracker crust.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Just before serving, top with ice cream or whipped cream.
May be frozen.

title: banana-chocolate chip loaf
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Cream margarine, vanilla and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture and bananas alternately to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and 2 teaspoons of salt; beat in cold water.
Place in one bowl.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
In a large bowl of Mixmaster, put in shortening and add boiling water. Stir until shortening is melted.
Put in egg mixture and yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Add flour gradually using slow speed of mixer.
Dough will be soft, but rolls are perfect.
Cover top of bowl with a greased, inverted plate and leave to double in bulk. Punch down.
Roll half of dough.
Cover rolled dough with melted butter.
Cut with biscuit cutter and fold over.
Butter tops and set to rise again.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes two 9 x 13-inch pans.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Coat cereal.
Layer cereal and sprinkle with powdered sugar (coat well with sugar).
This will use about 3/4 box of powdered sugar.
Store in closed airtight container.

title: chocolate cake-cream cheese filling
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour cake batter in greased sheet cake pan.
Beat together egg, sugar and softened cream cheese.
Spoon cheese mixture over cake and swirl with knife.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed brussels sprouts
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts according to package directions until barely tender.
Cool; cut a small hollow in each from the top. Fill with favorite cheese spread.
May be frozen and defrosted in refrigerator before serving.

title: mexican-beef cabbage
directions: Put oil in large skillet over moderate heat.
Add onion and saute until golden.
Add meat, cooking until brown.
Arrange cabbage over meat.
Add tomato sauce, garlic powder and pepper. Stir to blend.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes or until cabbage is just crisp-tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Serve over rice.

title: tandy cake
directions: Scald milk.
Add butter to milk.
Add this mixture to eggs. Then add flour, sugar, baking powder and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Spread peanut butter on top of cake while hot.
Then cool and pour melted chocolate chips on top.

title: daiquiri pie
directions: Stir pudding, gelatin, sugar, 1/2 cup water and eggs in saucepan. Blend well.
Then add remaining water. Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in rum.
Chill about 1 1/2 hours.
To hasten, chill and place bowl of mix in large bowl of ice and water.
Stir until mix is cold. Blend Cool Whip into chilled mix.
Spoon into crust.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Place a layer of waxed paper over a cookie sheet.
Set aside. Over medium heat, melt down milk and chocolate chips.
When thoroughly melted, add peanut butter chips.
Stir until mixed (not melted).
Put on waxed paper and spread.
Cool in refrigerator 15 minutes.
Cut into squares and put back into refrigerator until completely cool.

title: lo-cal sliced potato casserole
directions: Place all ingredients, except parsley, in a covered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Makes 6 servings.
One serving equals 75 calories.

title: caramel sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet.
Add brown sugar and heat over medium heat until sugar is melted.
Add nuts and spread potatoes in skillet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Invert on hot serving dish.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes.

Add sugar (gradually), pumpkin and lemon juice. Sift together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and baking powder. Fold into egg mixture. Spread on a jelly roll pan (10 x 15) lined with parchment paper. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: moroccan-style salmon with tomato sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in stick-free medium skillet with cooking spray and olive oil, over medium heat, until golden.
Stir in tomatoes (liquid included), honey, lemon peel and cumin. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly thick.
Meanwhile, season salmon with a trace of salt, pepper, paprika and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then broil for 10 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: brownie pizza(child's recipe)
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on box except pour mixture onto a pizza pan.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add all ingredients and simmer over low heat.
If using onions and/or green peppers, cook these with hamburger.

title: "king ranch" chicken
directions: This is a great crowd pleaser and I do believe every woman in Texas has this recipe.

title: nut tarts
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Mix with flour to form dough.
Roll dough into small balls (1 inch).
Place in small muffin cups. Chill while making filling.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, vegetables, soup, cheese, onions and seasoned salt.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake, covered, with lid or aluminum foil.
Remove from oven.
Cut crescent rolls into strips and place on top of casserole like lattice.
Put back into the oven and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Remove and serve.

title: date squares
directions: Mix dates, pecans, vanilla, sugar and eggs. Sift together and add baking powder, flour and salt. Bake in a shallow greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: my mother's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with foil. Coat foil with nonstick cooking spray.

title: cooked mixed vegetables
directions: Bring water, salt and margarine to boil.
Add vegetables. Bring to boil again and turn heat down low.
Simmer until all vegetables are tender (about 15 minutes).
Serve while hot.

title: daffodil lemon sauce
directions: Great topping for bread pudding!
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and nutmeg, gradually stir in water.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until thick and clear.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks, then return to hot mixture.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add butter or margarine, grated lemon peel and lemon juice; blend thoroughly.

title: parmesan squares
directions: Remove crust and cut bread slices into four pieces each.
Mix mayonnaise with chopped onion and spread on bread squares.
Place on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil until golden brown.
Watch carefully so as not to burn.
Serve immediately.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix meat, sauce, cottage cheese, eggs and other seasonings together.
Layer in a greased 10 x 13-inch pan as follows:
uncooked noodles, Mozzarella cheese and meat mixture; repeat.
Pour 1/4 cup water around edge.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° in preheated oven.
Uncover; garnish with more grated Mozzarella cheese and bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and let set 15 or 20 minutes.
(Easy to make one-half recipe.)

title: hog's head cheese
directions: Place pig's head, feet and ears in a large deep pot.
Add water to cover.
Add all seasonings except vinegar.
Cover pot, boil over low heat 2 to 3 hours until meat leaves bone.
Mince meat coarsely. Arrange in mold or pan.
Add vinegar to juice remaining in pot. Pour this liquid over meat in mold.
Refrigerate until mold has set or congealed.
When cold, slice and serve.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Melt butter in a large bowl.
Add 1 c. water and salt.
Stir. Add eggs and stir.
Dissolve yeast in 3 tsp. water.
Add yeast and sugar to mix and stir well.
Add flour & stir.
Knead dough on a floured surface.
Place dough in a buttered bowl.
Cover with a towel and let rise for 3 hours or until doubled in size.
Punch down dough and shape to desired shape.
Place in Pam sprayed pans, cover and let rise for 3 more hours.
Bake at 350° for 12-15 mins. Brush with melted butter immediately out of oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 350° oven until done.

title: island treasures(marinated shrimp)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shrimp.
Bring to rapid boil for 2 minutes; cool to room temperature.
Cover shrimp with marinade; chill for 3 hours.
Drain shrimp and serve.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to
box directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured
pan,
for
specified time on box. Remove and while cake is still hot, poke holes all over with a meat fork.
Spoon
pineapple
and
juice evenly on top.
Cool. Combine pudding mix
and
milk for pudding.
Add Cool Whip and spread evenly
over
cake.
Sprinkle
with
chopped
nuts
and coconut.

title: hunter's snack mix
directions: Pour oil mixture over and
mix	well.
Bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring often.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: At room temperature blend cheese, sausage and Bisquick.
Mix well. Form into balls (marble size).
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: italian marinated vegetables
directions: Combine all vegetables except tomatoes and parsley in large bowl.
Heat vinegar; stir in seasonings.
Cool slightly.
Combine with oil and pour over vegetables and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours, before serving.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Beat together sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and blend.
Add M&M's candies.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; remove stems and chop them finely.
Brown sausage and drain.
Add rest of ingredients, including stems, to sausage and form into small balls.
Place into mushroom caps. Heat at 350° for 6 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Drain cherries; keep juice and add lemon juice.
Cook until boils; add jello and ice in blender at high speed.
Pour in serving dish; top with sour cream and cherries.

title: orange jelled salad
directions: Empty pineapple in saucepan; add sugar and bring to a boil. Add jello; stir until dissolved. Add water and ice; stir.
Pour into a bowl and let set in the refrigerator until beginning to thicken.
Fold in nuts, cheese and Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: crunchy tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine noodles, soup and sour cream. Add peas and carrots, mushrooms, tuna, thyme, pepper and salt. Pour into an oiled 2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: a meal
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Pour off grease.
Place in baking dish.
Drain green beans and put on top of hamburger.
Lay thin slices of Velveeta cheese over green beans.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Pour soup over top and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: oreo cake
directions: Melt oleo and add crumbled Oreos except 6 Oreos, crumbled, for top.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: pig licking cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Add pineapple.
Combine 1/2 cup pineapple and vanilla instant pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: tropical dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain crushed pineapple and spread on bottom of a lightly greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit. Dot evenly with margarine. Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: a whimsical cake(quick and easy)
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl, including the juice from fruit cocktail.
Stir until well blended, then pour into buttered and floured large tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours or until dry when tested.
I sprinkle top with powdered sugar.
You can make a thin icing, if you prefer.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: Grill or broil chicken and cut into bite sized pieces.
Set aside.
Cook pasta per package directions and drain.
Melt butter. Add milk, egg and cheeses.
Cook until melted.
Add pasta, chicken and seasonings to taste.

title: finger salad
directions: Press crescent rolls in jelly roll pan (11 x 15-inch).
Bake and cool.
Mix cream cheese, Hidden Valley dressing mix and mayonnaise with a mixer until smooth.
Spread on dough.
Sprinkle vegetables on cream cheese mix.
Press in lightly.
Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese and refrigerate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cool.
Add cheese, biscuit mix and water.
Mix until just blended.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: post toasties cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add dry ingredients.
Then fold in corn flakes and nuts.
Roll in balls and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: baked sandwiches
directions: Lay 8 slices of sandwich bread in a well-greased glass baking dish.
Put ham or Canadian bacon on bread.
Add slices of cheese. Top with other slices of bread.
Beat eggs with milk; add dry mustard and salt.
Pour over sandwiches and let stand overnight in fridge.
Sprinkle with corn flakes or Special K, mixed with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple wedge dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Stir in pineapple, dates and nuts.
Cover and refrigerate up to 48 hours.
Serve with apple wedges.
Makes 2 cups.
Also good with pears.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form into a ball.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle heavy (roll ball in dressing mix, then French's seasoned pepper).
Serve with cracker of your choice.

title: vinegar chess pie
directions: Melt margarine; allow to cool.
Mix all together and pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until set and crust is brown.

title: california avocado salsa
directions: In a bowl, Combine the first 8 ingredients and mix well. Serve immediately with chips. Makes 5 cups.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Spread crumbs over top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: willie's dish
directions: Cook at medium heat until macaroni gets done.
Add cheese before serving (optional).

title: caramel pie
directions: Melt butter, coconut and pecans; toast until golden brown. Then cool.
Combine cream cheese and milk; beat until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer 1/4 cream cheese mixture in each pie shell; add a layer of coconut mixture.
Drizzle caramel topping over it.
(Heat topping in a microwave 30 to 40 seconds in a jar.) Layer until filled; keep in freezer until 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Chop mushroom stems only and onion, saute in butter or margarine.
Add crushed crackers (2 rolls) to sauteed mixture, continue stirring over heat.
Add shredded cheese a little at a time, continue stirring.
When all cheese is melted into mixture, spoon into caps of mushrooms.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes or until brown. A great party appetizer, you'll be a hit!

title: salmon patties
directions: Put salmon in a dish.
You may remove bone and skin.
Add whipped egg, onion, celery, carrot, butter and crackers.
If dry, add a little milk.
Blend well.
Make into patties.
Fry on both sides until brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Put in pot and add tomato sauce, water and spices.
Cover and simmer, the longer the better.
To thicken chili, mix in a jar 1/4 cup of water and flour.
Shake to get out lumps.
Use as needed.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cream and beat as a cake.
Put in a well-greased baking dish.

title: fried eggplant or zucchini(ca 1940's wartime)
directions: Cut vegetable into 1/2-inch slices.
Pare and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Lay slice upon slice and place a plate upon the top.
Let stand about 2 hours.
The salt will draw out the bitter flavor.
A half hour before serving, wipe each slice dry.
Dip in beaten egg, then in cracker dust and saute in hot fat.
Put a pan in the oven or other place where it can be kept hot; lay a piece of absorbent paper in the pan and upon it place the slices as they come crisp and brown from the frying pan.
Serve on a hot platter with slices overlapping.

title: mounds candy
directions: To the	milk
and margarine, add the powdered sugar and coconut.
Chill.
Make
into balls.
Put onto cookie sheet and cool again.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Fold into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Roll into balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bloody mary mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Chill 8 hours.
Serve with vodka and ice; garnish with dill pickle spears, celery heart stalks, etc.

title: emerald isle stew
directions: In Dutch oven, medium heat, heat oil until hot; add beef. Cook and stir until browned on all sides.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until meat and veggies are tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spoon into 9-inch graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine eggs, milk, Flapjax mix, sugar and vanilla in medium bowl; mix until smooth.
Heat oil to 375° in heavy skillet.
Spoon 1/4 cup batter into funnel, holding finger over funnel opening. Release batter into hot oil in spiral, starting from center.
Fry until golden brown on both sides; drain on paper towel.
Repeat with remaining batter.
Sprinkle generously with confectioners sugar.
Serve warm.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: heart healthy chicken marinade
directions: Mix together; add boneless, skinless chicken breasts. Marinate for the day.
Cook chicken on grill or in broiler.

title: scrumptious chocolate dessert
directions: Mix flour and melted margarine together in a baking dish. Bake at 325° until golden brown. Let cool. Mix the powdered sugar, 1/2 of the Cool Whip and cream cheese together.
Spread over crust.
Mix chocolate pudding as directed on package. Spread over last layer. Spread remaining Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle chocolate chips or nuts on top.
Cool and serve. A very good and simple recipe.

title: hidden valley ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Drain vegetables and blot dry on paper towels.
Sprinkle equal amounts of remaining ingredients on top cream cheese.
Roll tortillas tightly.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut rolls into 1-inch pieces. Makes 3 dozen.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together eggs, cornbread mix and milk and set aside.
Pour half cornbread mixture in sheet pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour in pan.
Pour remaining cornbread mixture in top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: eskimo cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and cocoa together until they are thoroughly blended.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls about 2 cm diameter.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Chill in refrigerator about 1 hour.
Makes about 80 cookies.

title: eggless pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, marshmallows, cinnamon and salt in top of double boiler.
Stir constantly until marshmallows are melted. Remove from heat and chill thoroughly.
Whip cream.
Beat pumpkin mixture until fluffy, then fold in whipped cream.
Pour into baked pie shell and refrigerate.

title: escarole soup
directions: Prepare little meatballs and fry until brown.
Boil escarole. Next run it under cold water and strain.
Chop escarole into small pieces.
Add meatballs and escarole to broth and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Beat eggs and add Parmesan cheese.
Add egg mixture to broth.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 20 minutes.
Stir and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: applesauce
directions: Combine all ingredients to taste.

title: goulash
directions: Brown the meat in oil or butter.
Add the onions and fry until the onions are translucent.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Put chicken in an oblong pan.
Mix ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna cheese biscuit bake(casserole)
directions: Arrange biscuits in ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream
butter.	Add
sugars, egg, flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix,
roll
and chill (can freeze).
Slice.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
(May be cut in any size or shape.)

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a large casserole.
Wash and remove excess fat from chops and dry.
Peel and slice potatoes 1/8 to 1/4-inch; layer on bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle with flour, butter dabs, salt, pepper, garlic and onion powders.
Cover with Velveeta slices.
Top cheese with pork chops; season again.
Layer remaining potatoes; repeat ingredients, layering as before.
Top with more cheese slices.
Add most of the milk to casserole to bake 1 1/4 hours.
Halfway through, bring pork chops to top for browning.
Stir potatoes; add more milk for au gratin consistency. Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a well-greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook the corn on the cob for 20 minutes. Remove corn from cob. Cook all ingredients together about 30 minutes.
Put in jars. Heat in water bath and seal.

title: tuna plate
directions: Blend together.
Pack into a small bowl or mold and chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Invert on a serving platter and surround with crackers or wedges of pita bread.
For variety, replace chili sauce with one of the following: well-drained relish, soy sauce or salad dressing.
Whatever you add, be sure basic cheese and tuna mixture remains thick enough to firm by chilling.

title: original chex party mix(microwave recipe)
directions: In small bowl, add Lawry's seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce to melted margarine; mix well.
Pour Chex cereals, nuts and pretzels into large resealable plastic bag.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture inside bag.
Seal top securely.
Shake bag until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour contents of bag into large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool. Store in resealable plastic bag or airtight container.
Makes 9 cups.

title: elaina's favorite strawberry muffins
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Mix all ingredients except pecans with an electric mixer.
Fold in nuts.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups.
Bake at 350° for 22 to 25 minutes.
Use toothpick test for doneness.
Makes approximately 15 average sized muffins.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cut the vegetables.
Place in a large pot with 2 cups of water.
Broil for at least 30 minutes.
Add the 4 cans of tomato sauce.
Fry the pound of beef.
Add the beef to the pot.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: green tea banana slush
directions: In saucepan, bring water and sugar to a boil; remove from heat. Add tea bags and brew for 1 1/2 minutes, dunking bags occasionally. Remove tea bags and chill. In a blender, process all ingredients at high speed until blended.
Pour into frosty glass. Garnish, if desired with whipped cream and mint twigs and serve.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Cream eggs, oil and sugar; add pineapple and zucchini.
Then add dry ingredients.
I sometimes add more flour (up to 1/2 cup). Add nuts and raisins last.
I like a stiff batter, so if it's too soft or runny, add more flour.
Prepare bread pans (I line the bottom and sides with wax paper).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 "fat" or 3 "skinny" loaves of bread.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Mash bananas.
Add cream, sugar, eggs, flavoring and butter.
Blend.
Add nuts.
Pour over flour mixture and beat.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Heat the first 2 ingredients until sugar and Karo syrup are clear. Remove from heat.
Mix in the peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Spread in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
May be iced with chocolate frosting.
Cut while warm.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mix the sour cream, mayo and taco mix.
Place on a large platter or glass baking dish, layer by layer.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: tuna delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil a 1-quart loaf pan.
Combine the tuna, saltines, margarine, eggs, onion, green pepper, Worcestershire sauce and juice.
Mix well (use food processor if you wish).
Press into loaf pan and bake for about 35 minutes. Serves 4.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and vinegar and cook over hot water until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients, folding in whipped cream last.
Fold entire mixture into cool custard.
Pour into molds or Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate until entirely cold.
Cut into squares.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Crumble ground beef in 2-quart (12 x 7-inch) glass baking dish.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Drain and stir in salt, spaghetti mix, tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Mix well.

title: quick and easy meal
directions: Shred lettuce into bowl.
Add onion, eggs, and tuna.
Mix some salad dressing with sugar and vinegar.
Add a little milk; pour over salad.
Mix well; serve with fried potatoes.

title: batter bread
directions: Soften yeast in sugar and water.
Add shortening, salt and 1/2 of the flour.
Use mixer and beat well.
Add rest of flour. Scrape sides of bowl and cover; let rise 30 minutes.
Stir well with spoon and pour into greased pan.
Let rise for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Put all ingredients in large plastic bag; shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty into shallow baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put French-style
beans,
cream of mushroom and chopped onion in microwave
for
approximately 5 minutes.
Take out of microwave and
stir these preheated ingredients.
Reset microwave 10 minutes or
until
onion
is tender.
Top with French fried onions and place
in
microwave
for 3 last minutes and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pizza biscuits
directions: Add tomato paste to ground beef mixture.
Then onion flakes, salt and Italian seasoning.
Press biscuits into muffin pan.
Fill with meat mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Cook vinegar, sugar and soy sauce. Cool and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: kielbasa with apples(microwave)
directions: You know, the large, yellow, oval-shaped vegetable - so named because the fruit separates into spaghetti-like strands.
The texture is crunchy and weight watchers may eat unlimited amounts.

title: tea cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add 1 egg at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add flour, baking
powder, salt and vanilla. Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375 degrees until slightly brown.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: In a saucepan, combine 1 cup vinegar, 3/4 cup oil, 2 teaspoons sugar, 1 teaspoon dry mustard, 1 teaspoon celery seed and 1 tablespoon salt; bring to a boil.
In a bowl, combine cabbage and onions (sliced).
Toss with 7/8 cup sugar.
Pour mixture over cabbage and onions.
Toss while cooling.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Lasts 1 to 2 weeks in refrigerator.
It is better after it marinates 24 hours.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine. Combine onion, rice and rest of ingredients.
Stir until cheese melts. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: gourmet potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potatoes.
Pour mixture over potatoes and toss.
Chill several hours.
Serves 12.

title: jello yogurt pie
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups hot water with Jell-O.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Mix in blender or with eggbeater the Jell-O and yogurt.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip and appropriate fruits.

title: light 'n crispy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients: white and brown sugars, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Add butter, oil, egg and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour and milk.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Gently fold in flour, baking soda, cocoa, salt and food coloring.
Pour batter in two well-greased cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Leave in pan 10 minutes.
Frost cake with favorite frosting.

title: frozen applesauce 'n' fruit cup
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Spoon fruit mixture into individual dishes.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer about 30 minutes before serving.
Garnish if desired.
Makes 7 servings, 3 1/2 cups.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 cup of the sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt in double boiler.
Add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Cover; cook for 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks with the 1/2 cup sugar.
Gradually pour the hot mixture over it.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Add lemon juice and rind just before removing from heat.
Mix well.
Cool.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue of egg whites.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping; blend well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours. Garnish with fruit toppings such as canned blueberries, mandarin oranges (drained) or canned cherries.

title: mushroom dip
directions: Cook mushrooms and onion in butter.
Add flour and salt and cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add sour cream and cheese.
Garnish with paprika.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch bits in double boiler.
In large pan, combine sugar and syrup.
Cook over low heat until just coming to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies. Press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
(Use wax paper to press evenly in pan.)
Spread melted chocolate over mixture. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut into bars.
(If sticky, refrigerate longer.
If too hard, let stand about 5 minutes.)

title: creamy shells with broccoli and ham
directions: Cook shells in boiling salted water according to package directions.
Slice ham into slivers; cut broccoli into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix flour with half of sugar.
Add boiling water and cook 15 minutes.
Add rest of sugar and beaten egg yolks; cook a few minutes longer.
Add butter, vinegar and 1 teaspoon lemon extract, if desired.

title: batter-fried vegetables
directions: In bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients.
Stir in water and egg until smooth.
Pour corn oil into large skillet to depth of 1/2-inch, filling no more than 1/3 full.
Heat over medium heat to 375°.
Dip vegetables a few at a time into batter; carefully add vegetables to hot oil, a few pieces at a time.
Fry, turning once, 2 or 3 minutes or until golden brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towel.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Make a layer of crumbs, oysters and soup.
Repeat until all is used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: evelyn's vegetable fry
directions: Take equal parts of vegetables.
Batter together in corn meal. Fry in oil.
Salt and pepper.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale and chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse kidney beans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
